      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>18 threads, <a href=/journal2.html?user=189461&start=0>1</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;</td></tr></table></form><ul>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f106114652963530>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=106114652963530>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=106114652963530>Reckoning  #17</a> <a id=fs8 href=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=106114652963530#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Aug 17th 2:57 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189461><span id=Sage>Taimarawee</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.06]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Reckoning #17<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br> ****Watching this strange wonder it holds so gently-soon realizes it CANNOT Kill this ‘LivingThing!’ Soft curves - warm flesh, an Earth smell of delicious scent surrounds this creature! Confusion sets its mind chasing down a path it has never experienced before! Solidifying its Ebony-Blackened mass..Wants comfort for this LivingThing it embraces. Why has it has brought these two ‘LivingThings’ to ITS secret Lair? Was it to keep away from the ‘Master’?? Hissing its irration…Quivers as it senses the other ‘LivingThing’ stirring…This ONE it does want to KILL!****<br><br>****Slowly I rise – following a coned hazy light, beckoning from above. Bitter pain..Almost my minds undoing! Tredipation pounding heavily within my chest, open my eyes!<br><br>Vision stilted, Darrien looks to his surroundings. “Where am I?” – “This is NOT where we were!!”<br>Forest green eyes adjusting to the dim cavern light, gasps with macabre horror! Floating easily with the warm air currents of this vast cavern is the Shadow – Its massive bulk holds, as if in a lovers embrace, CHAZ’ET! Limp - prone across its razored tentacles! Her beautiful sapphire robe, dirty, torn – split up one side, exposing to Darrien’s shocked sight, massive bruising along her thigh! Spun-Silver hair flows the current – lapping the filthy dirt floor beneath! Once radiant Tier’dal skin NOW ashen in color!!<br><br>Darrien’s thoughts rampage with hatred for this Shadow!! Deep feelings of possession.. love{?}.. jealousy.. tears his soul! – His heart lurches...! <br>“NAY Shadow!” “The ‘LivingThing’ you hold so tenderly, is MINE!!” Stripped - by the ‘Master’ - of everything it held close – the Shadow understands ‘All to Clearly’ the meaning from the other ‘LivingThing’!!<br><br>Tithering..It glides rear-wards from the threat, of losing its warm possession! Darrien’s attention is drawn to the cavern floor. “Gods!” “Not AGAIN!!” Lying serene – brilliantly displaying itself is: Shal’ette! OUT of his REACH!!<br><br>‘Battle Reaction’ -- to his swords call – finds unconsciousness threating once more! “Whoa!!” -“Steady there Ranger!!” Nausea has his insides churning a Tango of forthcoming bile.. Should he pursue this venture too quickly!! Instinct tells him - for the moment - Chaz’et is safe.. takes full inventory of his injuries -- Discovers no harm, other than a large swelling knot to the back of his head!! <br><br>Narrowing his vision, to see more clearly through the caverns muggy mist, takes halting steps, zeroing in on Shal’ette! For every step Darrien pursues, the Shadow is forced rear-wards to accommodate this Ranger!! “AYE!” “Tis Good!” – “Back with ye Black Death!!”<br><br>Restless-Irritated-Possessive of its prize, the Shadow elongates one of its tentacles.. aiming towards its hated enemy! Its razored-edge slicing deep into Chaz’et as it grows!! Chaz’et moaning deeply with the fiery burning pain lancing her side!! Consequence resultant-HALTS-both Shadow &amp; Ranger!!<br><br>Raw tension escalating with every breathe Darrien takes! -- One will not give ground to the other!! * An idea dawns, almost knocking Darrien over with its intensity!* He senses the Shadow desires BOTH Chaz’et &amp; Shal’ette equally –“SHADOW!” “Give me leave to my sword” – “I give you leave of -‘MY’- ‘LivingThing’ you hold!!”<br><br>**It is FREELY being given something it DESIRES?!?!**<br>The Shadow hesitiates – It ALSO prizes the Silver Object before it!! Seeing his plan crumbling before him, rages – “AYE THEN!” “It is my sword you lust after?!?” “DONE!!”<br><br>“NOW!.. Drop your possession FOR IT!!!” “One way OR the other swirling death”.. “I will have my way ON THIS!!”<br><br>The Shadow shrilly hisses its frustration!! It Can Not fight back with Chaz’et in its embrace..!! Receding, gives Darrien ground to his sword! It watches with sorrow, as the other ‘LivingThing’ dominates the beautiful silvered prize!! Contracting – Expanding with burning hatred for the other – it is NOT aware what severe harm this is causing to what it holds!! <br><br>*Chaz’et being near crushed in pulsating blackness…Awakens!! The Shadow feeling movement of his ‘LivingThing’ reacts!! <br>NO!!! This one ‘NOT’ get away from me!! Instantly, the Shadow enfolds Chaz’et within itself, attempting to join with her!!<br><br>Hysteria - approaching madness - dwells inside those stricken Violet eyes!! Shadow &amp; Necromancer emerge as ONE!! <br><br>“NAY-MY GOD’S-NAY!!!” Fight the Shadow my Love!!” “DO NOT let it CONSUME YOU!!!” “Use your ‘Evil-Born’… “NOW CHAZ’ET!--PLEASE!!!”<br><br>*The Shadow winces!! Evil Incarnate greater than its own, crawls its blackened heart!! Hell’s Furnace ignites misery within its chest!! The Shadow shrieks its excruciating pain to the ‘Master’!!! 'It' receives NO answer!! <br><br>*Chaz’et’s mind has flown…Gone to her evil gods for protection! Crashing-tidal waves of deadly spell torment to the Shadow..release Chaz’ets body - slamming her to the hard Earth below!! Ribs break—blood pours to fragile paper-thin lungs!!!<br><br>As the Shadow dances a tune with 'Brother-Death' -- Chaz’et rises from the moldy cold ground, hatred encompassing her!!<br><br>Shocked! Darrien watches – As Tier’dal blood flows from ruby lips!… Pooling to her upturned palms below! White hot flames-give birth-changing hue to intense Burgundy-Red, as they marry to Chaz’ets blooded up-turned palms – thrumming greedily they ‘AWAIT’ the Kill!!!<br>Electricity oozing from her very pores, bears forth jagged lightening hovering beside Chaz’ets lush battered body! Kissing ancient dirt - zigzags the cavern with horrendous power - It awaits its ‘Mistress’ call!!<br><br>Darrien, snapping out of his hypnotic prison - watching her transformation.. Rushes to her side – to be swatted aside, like a loathsome pest!!<br><br>*Harsh Evil winds fly the cavern, building tempo with each passing!! Dirt – rocks – putrid moss fly near its zenith!! Hard-packed Earth groans protest!.. Granite walls split asunder - sounding of whip-to-flayed-skin… Bleeding forth hideous creatures the mind best NOT dwell upon!!<br><br>Chaz’et, devoured by her evil gods - arrows forth twin arcs of blood-licked molten flame…’GUTS’ the Shadow!!! Aflame, its un-nerving wail re-bounds cavern walls, driving Darrien flat to the earth, desperately trying to cover his ears, before hearing will be stripped from him!!!<br>Commanding her eerie ozone-stench lightening – sends it slamming to the ceiling on high!! Massive chunks of ancient earth explode - pummeling the Shadow below… Burying the ONE who had ‘DARED’ embrace HER!!!<br><br>~~Buried deep within its boulder prison, heaving its last… Wings its dying thoughts to its ‘LivingThing’ – of - gratitude - releasing it from Hell &amp; Misery born too long!~~<br><br>*As suffocating debris begins to clear – all the sound you hear is--pulverized granite pebbles trickling down from the wounded cavern ceiling to lie at Chaz’et’s bloodied feet. Silence is acute! – Too much so!! - For the chaos that had reigned only moments ago!!!**<br><br>*Darrien - barely in time - catches Chaz’et as she collapses from sheer exhaustion! Red-rimmed-Violet eyes, roll back in that beautiful face! Tier’dal skin, once shimmering-begging to be caressed-is now more sickly gray! Her breathing, labored – ragged, wet with blood! <br>*Overpowering grief, numbing his soul.. Draws Chaz’et’s body to his chest - burying his face to silken hair-smelling richly still of Jasmine! “NAY! – DARK LADY!!” – “You will NOT leave me!!” “I forbid IT!!” -- Crystal tears trace bizarre patterns down rugged cheeks, now covered with Chaz’ets warm blood!<br><br>Wracked, gurgling-coughing brings Chaz’et back from her ‘Evil-Born’… hot tears of Darrien awash to her lovely face! Love-lorn eyes - Majestic Violet, see despair emulating his ravished face! …Soft whispering bids him closer to hear her!<br><br>“Darrien, my Ranger-Love”… “My lungs have been pierced by bone!” “I know not, how long I stay this plane!” “As I drifted in the Shadows deadly embrace”… ”I heard your call to me—to Fight Back!” “In the hearing of this”… “Gave me strength - to ‘Fight for US’ - my love!” “This time ONLY, do I acknowledge my Evil Gods for my Dark Arts!!” ~ Deep-unending love for this Ranger, pushes her endurance further still!!<br><br>Blood loss is severe!!! -- ‘As if in a Dream’… Chaz'et raises her spell-scorched dainty hand, seeking - touching - caressing his tear-stained cheek! This Necromancer burns to memory, his forest-smell – ever present - his rich deep voice, sparking shivers of desire when she hears it - feels how he tenderly embraces her now! <br>A sad smile curves blood-moist ruby lips &amp; knows these memories will have to hold--for all eternity! “I regret my hurting of you my love”… ”It could not be helped!” “I have no will against my ‘Evil-Born’ when I call it to me.”<br><br>“Pleasee,” she pauses, violently coughing up foamy rich blood – “Forgive - Mee”……..<br><br>~~Spiritless.. That dainty Tier’dal hand falls limply to her chest!!~~<br><br>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br><br>”NAYYY!!!”~~~Darrien’s pain is ‘TOO GREAT’!! Throwing back rich chestnut hair, screams his release of hellish pain consuming him!!!<br><br>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br><br>*This tortured, lost soul…does not move from her!! He WILL NOT let her GO!!*<br><br>~~Time Rests for this ‘One’~~ <br>Minutes tick to hours… Hours pass to yet-another day!!*<br><br>*Stoned Silence of a Grave, rests heavily, enshrouding this couple!<br><br>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br><br>*Darrien, in his heart-wrenching grief, hears NOT, --soft footsteps approaching behind him!!*<br><br>“MOVE from her RANGER—NOW!!”<br>Startled… Darrien--reluctionally comes BACK! “How long have I sat here??” – His anguished-mind refusing any of this!!! <br>“This is my last warning!” “Depart from Her!!”--“This Necromancer has ‘NOT’ yet traveled her death plane!”<br>“Why care ‘YOU’ Creature?!?”--“Needing another ‘PET’ are WE?!?... Darrien snarls thru gritted teeth! Heinous laughter-Darrien remembers all too well-erupts from spell-ravaged throat! “Nay Ranger”-“This one is too dangerous to be made a pet!!” “She proved her worth to ‘ME’, by killing a trouble-some Shadow I regretted binding to me!!” <br>~~~Hmmm… “I was correct!!” “I DO know this one!”.. “Is not her name Chaz’et Da`Linn – of the Royal ‘House Da`Linn?”<br>~“Aye rogue!”—“It be she”.. says a confused Darrien.<br><br>*Like a ghost, the Tier’dal glides forward – Darrien’s eyes deceiving to weather he walks the ground or no! Relenting to this Necromancer… places his 'DarkLady' as comfortable as he can, retreating from her, to gather Shal’ette.<br><br>*“Stay Yer Hand Ranger!!” “If my purpose had been death”... “You WOULD be dead now!!”<br><br>Reluctantly, sheathing Shal’ette, his stance on guard says: “Your part in this Tier’dal?!?” “SILENCE” Ranger!!” “I need to concentrate!!!”… Laying one Sore-Infested hand to Chaz’ets brow, the other to her stricken chest… begins to chant a language foreign to Darrien’s ears. Recoiling nausea crawls Darrien’s soul, as he witnesses this act!!<br><br>~~Darrien has come to a profound realization~~ he wants ‘No-Other’ touching her! -- Especially this foul monster!!!~~ <br><br>*Chanting -- *Humming rising...falling -- Foreign melody to his ears! Pale pulses of agate-brown magik drift the length of Chaz’et, caressing, healing! He hears a SNAP or CLICK, if you will, as Bones re-set! Her breathing less labored – Severe burns to her palms disappearing!<br><br>*Darrien is lulled by this foreign chanting… Drifting with the sound…Travels inward escaping his wounded mind. Wearyness rocks this Ranger--stripping him of his guard. No longer caring of himself – resolute to what could happen to him…’IF’ the Rogue Tier’dal turns on him!<br><br>*As Darrien is witness to ‘Death’ losing its battle--comprehends:--‘Resolution’!!! Holding Chaz’et as she lay dying in his arms - helpless to aid her - re-assigns where ‘FATE’ has always intended him to ‘BE’!! <br><br>*Repine heavily upon those great shoulders these weeks past, finds: ‘Azzarria,’ no longer binds his heart!! “Aye!”, he thinks… “Azzarria’ will always be with me” – “I will ne’er escape her beautiful ‘Huntress’ presence”…he muses!-- BUT -- Impotent he now is… To new love discovered… for the ‘DarkLady’ he had traveled beside!<br><br>~~Finality releases Darrien--Of a bonding long ago!!~~ <br><br>*Deep green eyes, hue deeper, as before him kneels his Chaz’et!!! Ecstatic happiness drowns this tempestuous Ranger!!!<br>Ranger-Chivalry lends a hand – the two rise as one, embracing! Lingering--passionate kisses, rekindling desire of the other once more!!<br><br>*“AHEM!!” Reluctantly moving apart – yet nestled within each other arms – wait for this Rogue’s Axe to fall!! “There be a PRICE you must pay Necromancer..to ME!!” <br>Darrien feels Chaz’et shiver within his warm embrace.. ”Aye!” - “What must I do?!?...Chaz’et whispers fearfully!<br><br>“Follow me to my Lair, Chaz’et” – “I DEMAND the proper knowledge of the poison-based spell….’YOU’ accomplished!” “I knew when I saw yer Pet wandering my Sewers.. what you were about!!” <br>“As is obvious before you”… ”You succeeded, where “I” had failed!!” <br>Gasping!.. Chaz’et NOW knows who this Tier’dal IS!!<br><br>*Complying to him – Completes her Debt!!<br><br>With ‘PRECIOUS’ knowledge gained of this dangerous spell – ‘which nearly killed him’ - Waves them leave.. To bother him NO further saying: “DO NOT return here Chaz’et!!” “I will NOT be as tolerant time next of yer presence!!!”<br><br>*Ranger &amp; Necromancer ascend from that foul place - breathing pure Valley air!!<br>*Neither believing until this wonderous moment…’ONE’ would be spared—the ‘OTHER’ find Love!!!<br><br>*In stealth, Darrien leads his 'DarkLady' afar from Qeynos harm…... <br><br>*This love-lost Ranger, lead by grateful heart – experiences with Chaz’et - his hidden place!<br>No other - even his ‘Azzarria’, had feasted upon this beauty!<br><br>*Rich lush forest beauty, serene — to soothe their battered souls – A dazzling waterfall - Rainbow’d for Chaz’ets delight – Playing its cascading ‘Love Song’ – To refresh &amp; heal their injured spirits!<br><br><br>~~Darrien anticipates the Star-Encrusted Night forthcoming -- To “Fully” explore Chaz’et’s enticing charms!!! <br>Knowing..too soon - the 'Past binding' to ‘Azzarria’ must be told to her!!~~<br><br><br>****”As in FairyTales” -- “Read to sleepy-children beside their warm fires, late onto the Night” – ‘True Love ‘DOES’ come to those Deserving of its: ‘Haunting Call’!!!”****<br><br><br>Chapter 17…..To be continued.<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Azzarria - "Stormchild"<br>"The Huntress"</td></tr>
