	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189461><span id=Sage>Taimarawee</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.06]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>***The Shadow wanders, pulsatile with irritability-edginess! It's fractured thoughts flow with explosive-helpless rage!!<br><br>Being summoned to aid in the capture &amp; torture of a unlucky Bloodsaber wandering alone through their Lair... STILL did NOT appease its 'Master'! Venomous-spitting spells-injuring grieviously the Shadow - Was its only thankless gift from this Insane Teir'dal!<br><br>***The Shadow was formed in these tunnels-through Greed, Deceit, Death, &amp; Wanton Destruction of all miscreants laying claim here-in! Over Centuries in Time it grew in bulk &amp; lewdness--engulfing all unfortunates who happened upon it! Its dense swirling blackness, pouncing-ensnaring! Ever sooo slowly--Digesting their Sweet-Salty flesh!<br><br>Without caution nor care--massive enjoyment of this depraved game, became common-place with the Shadow! THUS!! Leading to its capture by the 'Master'! Chained by deadly spells of the rouge Tier'dal--Endless Torment if it ever Disobeyed!<br><br>Sad--Abused--Lonely!! *No other exists to be its mate*<br><br>Memories of how it lost its freedom, begins Anew the violent pulsating! Swelling beyond its mass-limits - Leadened whip-lashing tentacles of agonizing torment, scar deeply the sickly moss encrusted walls of this gigantic hidden cavern! The air current sings with horrific screeching--as auriferous granite &amp; moldy dirt are violently raped from cavern walls, creating horripilation if one is near this vengeful chaos!!<br><br>*Having finally released its fury, remembers the 'Living Thing'!! Undulating-quivering, pure evil trilling throught-out its massive bulk goes once more in seach of it!<br><br>In its deviant search for its prey-heralds upon a 'Dead Thing' face down near a pool of stinking stagnant water. Within these waters, observes an object! Even for its simple mind-it admires ornate beauty when it sees it!<br>Tremulous light radiates elongated Silver--Spun Gold near its hilt, laying serenely at the bottom of this pool.<br>&quot;What is this??&quot; &quot;A treasure for ME perhaps??&quot; It knows not what the object is--But yearns for it none-the-less. &quot;Later!&quot; &quot;Must Play NOW!&quot; <br>*Marking it's territory.. Continues the Hunt!!*<br><br>***Looking to the snugged warm fire-lite room, a handsome head rises-from kissing passion-softened wine ruby lips of the woman beneath him.<br>Forest green eyes--burn deeply into Violet Magenta--holding each for a time!<br><br>Fighting to calm his inner turmoil, raises gently from her, sitting to the edge of their fevor-known bed. In Darrien's movements, exposes Chaz'et fully to his view!!<br>Shameless longing for this Dark Elf arises within his loins! Leisurely-his eyes wander the length of her. Admiring Opalized hair, spilling the bed and pillows with its rich fullness--Waterfall cascading to the warm tiled floor below! Her delicate elven features, arched brows, pouty wine rubied lips-still moist from their kissings!!<br>Darrien enraptured--watches the rapid rise and fall of her ample chest, admiring muscled, yet graceful limbs--tiny fragile feet-their nails tinted a becoming shade of scarlet-red!<br><br>Chaz'et can NOT move! It's like becoming mezmerized-held captive, by the &quot;King of Snakes!&quot; Ne'er to be released! NOR wanting too!! Darrien's heated gaze to her body making breathing quite difficult for her!!<br><br>Darrien fights for control over his rampaging emotions, wanting once more to take FULL possession of the women this time!!<br><br>***&quot;Azzarria&quot; fleetingly crosses his fevered thoughts--BUT--Are set adrift by the stunning vision before him!<br><br>&quot;Her Name?&quot; &quot;My Gods--what was her name??&quot; &quot;Aye!&quot; &quot;Chaz'et!&quot;--&quot;A bewitching female she be!&quot; &quot;I wonder-has this Dark Elf per-chance put a spell upon me?&quot; -- In thinking these random thoughts, a frown plays across his rugged brow. Chaz'et seeing this--flinches as if Struck!! Darrien, noticing this: &quot;Nay-Dark Beauty-Nay!!&quot; Reaching- cups that delicate elven face within his warm hands, drawing the now trembling Chaz'et to his chest, enfolding her. Whispering to her delicate ear: &quot;Never harm need you fear from me!&quot; &quot;YOU, my Dark Lady, healed my ravished body--Thus the Savior of this wounded Soul!!&quot; &quot;Eternally--You have my protection &amp; sword!&quot;<br><br>*In the saying of those words.. Remembering his Shal'ette--stiffens!!<br>Chaz'et looking up to him--&quot;What bothers you so, my Love??&quot;<br><br>&quot;An endearment of words from this One?&quot; &quot;Azzarria&quot;--my &quot;Huntress&quot;--Even you spoke NOT these words to me!!&quot; - &quot;In truth-what truely are your feelings of me??&quot;<br>Wretching his trouble-sum thoughts from these two women asks: &quot;Chaz'et-Where I be?&quot; &quot;I must take my leave, to find my sword!&quot; &quot;Shal'ette-she is One with me in all Battles!&quot; &quot;Magik Runes guard &amp; bind her to me alone!&quot; &quot;I fear for whom-ever tries to weild her..For they will Rue that day!!&quot;<br><br>Moving a safer distance away from this handsome Ranger says: &quot;I had you transported here to Shar Vahl.&quot; &quot;The 'Vah Shir' allowed my privacy to attempt yer heal.&quot; &quot;No questions asked--No answers need given!&quot;<br>Hesitating for only an instant..&quot;There is something I MUST tell you of me.&quot;---Knowing this tale may have her Ranger leave her, she still, with heavy-heart, continues!<br><br>&quot;Darrien&quot;-&quot;I am well versed in the 'Dark Arts of Necromantia.&quot;...Hastily proceeding, seeing those beautiful green eyes narrow slightly!<br>&quot;If you remember, I hail from Neriak--hated Tier'dal--by most!&quot; &quot;BUT&quot;, by some thrust of fate, I was born, of a good soul!&quot; &quot;Be this curse OR Gift, I know NOT!&quot;<br>&quot;When I was very young, asking too may questions of my people, my Noble Kin - The &quot;House Da`Linn&quot;, put a Death-Summons upon my young head!&quot; &quot;Were it not for my beloved friend 'Iaaki' - I would be NO MORE!&quot; Escaping my people, I was found alone-half starved, wandering the wilds of East Commons, by a Honored Warrior--gentle of heart!&quot; &quot;Took me under his roof--claiming me his own-born!&quot;<br>*Chaz'et having to re-live this nightmarish memory once more--finds to her embarrassment tears brimming her lovely eyes!!*<br><br>Darrien's heart lurches, in seeing this beautiful Necromancer humbled before him! &quot;Nay-Lady-Nay!&quot; &quot;No more explaining is needed!&quot; Grabbing her in a tight embrace, runs his fingers gently up &amp; down her back, soothing her hurts..till once more she calms.<br><br>Sniffling, brushing away crystal tears, knows there is ONE more thing she must tell him of her past! Stepping over to the warm-bricked hearth, bids him sit near her. Drawing upon a needed breathe, continues: &quot;When I was still young , I had the misfortune of losing my beloved foster Father to the Nasty-Tempered Sand Giants of South Desert Ro!&quot; -- &quot;If my memory serves, the giant he &amp; his men were hunting was named: 'Lorr'. &quot;The fighting was horrendous!&quot; &quot;My Proud Warrior Father, lost that battle..BUT NOT to he!!&quot;<br><br>Morning-Dawns clear &amp; bright--the Valley serene.&quot; &quot;I am tending our small garden, when I see my Father step out of our hut, wearing full gear &amp; his favorite weapon.&quot; &quot;Approaching to the North are his men, also geared--as if for battle!&quot; &quot;Looking to him, I ask where he travels?&quot; He--tells this 'Young-One'--Do not fret 'Lil-One&quot;..&quot;I go to hunt for our people &amp; the town of FreePort.&quot;<br>&quot;Placing a Kiss upon his leathered brow..&quot;In my innocense&quot;.. Dismiss the matter, returning to my garden.&quot;<br>&quot;Late afternoon arrives--Later still approaching Dusk!--I begin to worry!&quot; &quot;Finally!&quot;--Upon the horizon I see the men returning---Slowly??!&quot; &quot;A litter being carried by 4 of my Father's strongest men!&quot; &quot;Setting my basket of vegetables down for nights sup, run to greet my late returning Father!&quot; &quot;Drawing closer, I notice something un-natural of the man laid upon the litter--He is bent &amp; twisted un-naturally for human form!&quot; &quot;Panic rising within me, looks to find my Father for comfort!&quot; &quot;Where be my Father!?&quot; &quot;I am approached by Fathers favorite and best friend&quot;...&quot;He Lies There 'Lil-One'! Sorrow bleeds from those eyes I look upon!&quot; &quot;I DO NOT believe him!!&quot; &quot;Nay-Nay, please this CAN NOT BE!!&quot;---&quot;Aye&quot;.. 'Lil-One'.. &quot;It BE He!!&quot;<br><br>&quot;A roaring wind twists my mind inside-out!!&quot; 'I fall unconscious to the land!!&quot;<br><br>&quot;Taking a chill-I awake to sounds of women weeping, fire crackling, warriors heralding the 'War Cry of Men'!!<br>Stumbling blindly from our hut..I am picked up &amp; put atop my Father's best-friends heavy shoulders.&quot; &quot;As we walk towards my now dead Father--I am told the 'War-Tale of Death!!&quot;<br><br>&quot;In the near winning of Father's battle, he is drawn to a sound a short distance away--Telling his men to continue the attack of 'Lorr'--Goes to find the source of this strange new sound!&quot; &quot;Cresting a Dune, he finds he is face to face with none other than the Twin Brother.. &quot;Ah, the name escapess...... &quot;GORR&quot;, Chaz'et!!&quot; &quot;His name is &quot;GORR!!!&quot;<br>&quot;Aye-Darrien, that was his name!&quot;<br>Looking to her new love, sees he is drawn-white with fury!.. &quot;Should I quit my telling of this tale, Darrien??&quot;<br>Gritting his teeth, Darrien says: &quot;Nay Lass, continue.....&quot;<br><br>*Collecting herself once more*<br>&quot;As my Father crested the Dune... &quot;Gorr's punishment was horrendous to his body!!&quot;... &quot;Beating him senseless--Crushing him beneath his heavy feet!!&quot; &quot;As if that were NOT enough--Ripped his weapon arm from his body...Eating it where my father fell!!!&quot;<br>&quot;Try as they might, his men could not reach him in time!&quot; The Twin Sand Giants--vanishing to their sands, having Not been seen since!!&quot;<br><br>&quot;Sliding from those massive shoulders..My soul dies Inside!&quot; &quot;Walking apart from my adopted people-the Starless Night still ringing with screams of hatred, sorrow &amp; revenge-I leave behind my goodness..calling forth my 'Evil-born Soul' for respite!!&quot; &quot;My Evil-Gods grant me my deadly wish!!&quot;<br>Hell rains forth, splitting my heavens, drowning my gentile soul, consuming, ripping it apart--Replacing, rebuilding it for their own evil plans of ME!!&quot;<br><br>&quot;For many seasons Darrien, I traveled these lands, with No Heart--No Soul of Goodness!!&quot; &quot;Killing everything that got in my path!!&quot;<br>*A child was my salvation--Seeing her near her village, alone-unprotected--A lioness near her, awaiting the moment to strike!!&quot; &quot;Saving this 'Innocent' released my shriveled soul, from the tortured Evil-Born hell I willing created for it!!&quot;<br>*Thus began a WAR I fight every day of my existence--Evil-Born nipping, gnawing at my Gentled Soul, trying to find its way back IN!!&quot;<br><br>*White-Knuckled Darrien has sat silently near this woman, journeying with her, as her tale unfolded - The Pain &amp; Agony undergone for one so young in season - knowing they NOW share as ONE, exacting revenge for a Sand Giant named &quot;GORR!!&quot;<br><br>Taking her soft dark-skinned hand into his, pulls Chaz'et to her feet. &quot;Never hate from I Dark Lady--You were young--you understood NOT-what you did!!&quot; &quot;Bury it deep, as I have done--lest it eat you alive!&quot;<br>&quot;I also must be in a telling to you of secrets..Dark Lady!&quot; &quot;Alas, though, it must stay.. in the telling.. for a short time.&quot; &quot;I need your help at present..to guide me back to the sewers.. &quot;I need to find my battle sword!&quot;<br><br>Shock, widens Chaz'ets Violet eyes!!&quot; &quot;Nay Ranger!!&quot; -- &quot;You MUST NOT DO THIS!&quot; &quot;Hush now Lady-Love! - I must locate my sword, regardless the cost to me!!&quot;<br>Throwing herself into his warm embrace tears begin anew!<br><br>Something akin to love--yet not--wretches his heart--Squeezing till it near bursts within his chest!! &quot;This haunted Dark Lady will be my un-doing, if I am not careful!!&quot; <br>Resting his bearded chin atop her silken head - looks within himself - mind &amp; memories traveling to his home-land, wanting above all else to have his Father's voice speak to him of these troubling things - be they right OR wrong in the tellings!!&quot;<br>&quot;This &quot;Angel of Death&quot; has become dear to me!&quot; &quot;One moment she is Devil's Fury..The next A Fragile Flower!&quot; &quot;NOT to be crushed by me-NOR-any OTHER!&quot;<br><br>**An unspoken bond-has somehow-been sealed within these two hearts...Now beating as one!! Commitment - Contentment - Sacrifice they will unknowingly soon share!! **FATE has decreed it SO!!**<br><br>Pushing herself to arms-length brushing dampened silver hair from tear-stained cheeks nods her acceptence of Darrien' request of her.<br>*Together as 'One' - &quot;Neriak's Necromancer&quot;--&quot;Surefall Glade Ranger&quot;, depart Shar Vahl memory - blind to what awaits them!<br><br>Entering the secret entrance to the Sewer Tunnels below, look with absolute confusion to which putrifying tunnel to begin their seach! Darrien instinctively senses Shal'ette--BUT--&quot;BY MY GODS&quot;, which tunnel before me!! The farther they travel, the more lost they become! Even Chaz'et's Dark Dealings here, have never lead her this far in!<br><br>SUDDENLY!!...Darrien grabbing Chaz'ets arm puts his finger to his lips - stilling her!! Icy fingers of fear snake their way down Chaz'ets spine!! She senses Evil--Great EVIL near!! Crashing waves of IT, consuming the very air around the couple!!<br><br>***The Shadow stretches leisurely near the dank slimy ceiling above them!! Grotesque-yet-magnificent in design, IT is a 'Killing Expert' to any near its ebony blackness!! &quot;Ahhhh! - it rasps with glutenous glee!! &quot;The 'Living Thing' has come to ME--and--brought me its MATE!!&quot;<br><br>A horrific gutteral roar rampages down the tunnels, dislodging dirt &amp; putrid moss in its wake!! &quot;WHERE BE YOU SHADOW??&quot; &quot;YOU HAVE ESCAPED ME FOR THE LAST TIME!!&quot;<br><br>*A deadly razor-edged tentacle of shadow, elongates-reaching close to Darrien's neck! He would think it but a spider--if felt--jerks the killing tentacle swiftly back into itself!! Over-powering lust for death of its 'Master' snaps the embittered Shadow around, facing the unearthly roars of it's summoner!!<br>&quot;We--will play tag in -- but a moment, 'Living Thing'!! -- &quot;You Rest!!&quot;--&quot;I want you both fresh for the chase.. It hissesss!!&quot;<br><br>**A foul breeze catches the couples hair. Looking up--&quot;What..What was That??&quot; &quot;There is NO wind nor currents here!&quot; <br>Chaz'et sensing the passing of evil begs Darrien to leave this section immediately!! Nodding whole-heartily guides her to an Eastern tunnel, yet unexplored.<br><br>Eyes watering-choking on acidic moisture, Darrien sees ahead 'Two Things' <br>A dead Bloodsaber twisted, stiff with death...<br>A gleam of intense light-mirroring deep the stagnant waters of a pool - dazzling silvered rays glint the ceiling above!<br>Rushing forward, pulling Chaz'et more roughly than he intended, nears the pools slippery edge.<br><br>&quot;Shal'ette!&quot; -- &quot;Gods! &quot;I have found you!!&quot; As Darrien dives to rescue his great battle sword, Chaz'et rubbing her wrist..is suddenly struck by these names said by he: 'Shal'ette' -- 'Azzarria'?!? &quot;I&quot; must know more of these two!!&quot; &quot;One a pure Silver Mistress before him--the 'Other'?? <br>Hostility storms her lovely face, deepening her Tier'dal hue. &quot;AYE!!&quot; &quot;The OTHER!!&quot;<br><br>Holding Shal`ette possessively, treads water back to the pool's edge near Chaz'ets dainty feet... Hoping for a hand-up from his Dark Lady. HE Receives NONE!!<br><br>Looking up -- Finds dark questioning anger sparking from Violet eyes!! Hands on shapely hips says: &quot;Darrien, who be Azzarria?!?&quot; -- Ice flows as blood with this unanswered question!! Making Darrien almost drop his possession back to the foul waters beneath him!!!<br><br>&quot;Chaz'et, please help me depart these filthy waters--As I told you before, there is also a tale, I must speak to you!&quot;<br>Seeing truth, sorrow, love(?) - spoken through forest green eyes--reaches for Darrien's hand to assist.........<br><br>WHEN: A dead voice from across the pond -- colder than a grave's frozen earth, snarls nastily!!!<br>&quot;WELL-Well!! &quot;What have we here??&quot; &quot;A Necromancer..HELPING..A Ranger!?!? &quot;I&quot; think NOT!!!&quot;<br><br>Both turning as one - sees; A Tier'dal Necromancer--his skin badly scarred, burnt meat red-black! Festering sores, running freely down his aged-face --clearly visible, even from their great distance of him!!!<br>One eye is missing...WAIT!!! It is nestled atop his enormous twisted staff!! Nauseating in it's color of yellowish-green!! His body is bent - twisted, as if, an explosion had erupted from within!! NO lips has he -- Blinding, Ivory Teeth.. Ground to sharpened points.. EACH!! They sit to upper &amp; lower jaws--the lower slightly off centered!!<br><br>To terrify the couple further -- Pulsating abhorent Midnight Shadow hovers near its Master!! Light myst-to-dense swirling ebony-madness!! Agitated tentacles of horror - razored at tapered ends - undulating as if being held in restraint unwillingly!!!<br><br>Horror-shock-mind numbing fear embeds itself in Chaz'ets body!! Yet, once more, she reaches, pulling Darrien from the stagnant pool.<br><br>An ear-piercing wail comes from the lipless mouth of this monster!!! Then - Deep vicious laughter from a ravaged throut!! His impaled eye upon the twisted staff glows yellow!! Lowering his massive staff - sends forth misery &amp; hell -- blasting them both unconscious against the tunnel wall!!<br><br>**Wellll, my trouble-sum Pet--will these two suffice?!?&quot; &quot;Let us say it's my apology for your mis-treatment of the day from me!!&quot;<br>As the Unholy creature - once - Dark Elf - slips back to the darkness of his tunnels...Heinous laughter re-bounds down silent struck areas, alerting even the Worst of Men to: &quot;LEAVE IT BE!!!&quot;<br><br>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br><br>&quot;It seems&quot; - &quot;My Gracious Readers&quot; - **&quot;THE ONE** Chaz'et was told had DIED appalling, attempting the Poison-Based Spell - She Had Succeeded with... &quot;DID NOT DIE!!!!!&quot;<br>~~~~~~~&quot;Wickedly, I Taunt You ALL!!&quot;~~~~~~~<br>Ha-Ha-Ha-Ha-Ha!!!<br>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br><br>Darrien NOW has his Shal'ette back by his side!!!<br><br>Chaz'et is able to call forth her 'Evil-Born' - hoping against hope, it won't consume her!!!<br><br>&quot;What say Yea All??&quot;<br><br>&quot;Whom&quot; - Or - &quot;Should I say 'WHAT' will win this Battle..About to Begin..In these UnHoly Sewers!?!?!?&quot; <br><br>Part 16...To Be Continued <br><br>&quot;Azza&quot; -- &quot;StormChild&quot;<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Azzarria - "Stormchild"<br>"The Huntress"</td></tr>
