	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189461><span id=Sage>Taimarawee</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.06]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Dizzy and Fevered, Azzarria - fights within herself, to turn around and go back to that beautiful place of tranquility. Nay though! Fortune does not Yet smile upon this blue-eyed beauty!!<br><br>As she travels, her eyes look to the entrance of Blackburrow, knowing that it would be - but a short journeys travel through the hated Gnoll Lands, to once more, be with her Kin. Gods!! The yearning to set eyes on her beloved Father once more! To snuggle into his warm embrace and act the child, she once was! Having him kiss her pains and hurts away! &quot;Enough of This..Azzarria!&quot; To do so, would put her entire village in jeopardy! What I have done, I have done for the love of both my family and my Ranger! This now becomes my fight alone. I will not see the slaughter of innocents!<br><br>Traveling without thought now, Azzarria realizes. that she has passed the crossroads. Should she continue onto Qeynos and find a healer? In doing this, also per-chance, come upon outside help for her cause? Nay! Leave it!<br>Starting back, Azzarria makes her tracks confusing to follow. Hither and ther she wanders, knowing in her heart Darrien will soon follow! Having accomplished this deception, sets her course for the Wild Karana Lands.<br><br>Entering West Karana, she finds with her deception of her paths, at the crossroads...a lateness of the hour is near. Knowing dangerous creatures of untold horror and strength are now hunting, she sits to wait.<br>Azzarria's mind, now at rest, for a brief time, reflects on the days repast. -- &quot;Why must this be happening to me?&quot; &quot;Have I angered my Gods unknowingly?&quot; Looking within herself...decides, that Destiny and her Gods - fickle creatures they be - will guide her, when they are ready!<br><br>Sensing the danger has past, continues on...following the muddy river bank, instinct telling her to stay - passing through the heart of this land and leave the residents here to their own warrings!<br><br>Twice detained, having to fight &quot;Feathered Hells&quot; drifting with the winds..she sees the Granite Peaks of Highpass finally before her.<br>Moving to a relative place of safety and shelter, Azzarria makes camp for the night.<br><br>&quot;Now..Where did I put?&quot; --&quot;Ah, there you are.&quot; Pulling pungent sweetmeats from her pack, begins to quiet the rumblings of her belly. Trailjuice follows, making her smile, knowing from whence it came.<br>Once more, reaching into her pack, she finds her most treasured item. --Her &quot;soft blanket&quot;. Woven with the skill of many. Fibers so strong, yet soft..it's like running fingers through silky webbing. Bringing this treasure close to her face, she smells the scent of Pine and Darrien beginning to work its magik on her soul.<br><br>Stiffly, adjusting her position on the hard ground, the beastlord looks to her Heavens high above. Luclin's beautiful blue-white face, sauntering across the sky for her eyes pleasure.<br>Sighing, Azzarria rolls over and reaches for Ponpi', feeling - only emptiness where she touches. The dampness of the ground, matching the dampness emerging behind her closed tired eyes!<br><br>**Late in the night, a Strikeningly-Handsome Druid sits in the lea of a Wyntertree, filling his eyes with this beautiful, but troubled beastlord.<br>He has followed Azzarria from the Glades...As &quot;Brylin&quot; observes her tossings and turnings -- of nightmares known only to her --he reaches once more for his Ashwood Pipe. Smoke curling above his long deep chestnut hair - curly and damp, from the dew - Brylin reflects on his reaction, upon seeing her for the first time**<br><br>**Brylin steps out, weary of his Masters constant rebukes on he being entirely to wild and headstrong for his Druid ways. Drawing in the warm pine driven air, clears his mind and notices a commotion coming from the tunnel leading in.<br><br>What he sees before him, makes him step back, bumping hard into the tree behind him! Before his startled eyes.. Being carried..IS, &quot;A Vision of Pure Beauty!&quot; Never before has he seen a female as she! -- Tall, muscular..Yet soft curved. --Hair, the color of Burnt Autumn Red, wavey, caressing the ground with it long length!<br>Losing sight of her, Brylin knows...Master or NO...he has to see more of this heavenly creature!<br><br>Moving quickly...Almost toppling head first over a downed Rathbush in his haste!!<br>Chuckling to himself, he comes within distance, yet far enough away, not to disturb the Half-Elf Ranger carrying her. Listening to their conversation..Brylin learns her name is --&quot;Azzarria Zathla'een&quot;, barbarian beastlord, hailing from a remote vilage to the frozen North called &quot;Halas&quot;. <br>Brylin, had heard tellings of this remote area and in due course, was planning a journey there. NOW, he had wished it had been planned sooner!!!<br><br>Something was happening to this Druid! --Yearnings to gather this wild beauty in his arms! To soothe her hurts, to heal her wounds...became an obsession within him!<br>&quot;Destiny&quot;, once more was at play here! &quot;HIS&quot; Heart also, was NOW lost forever to this woman!!<br><br>Azzarria, turning in her sleep, was now facing his position in the Wyntertree. Once more, Brylin saw her reach out and sigh.<br>What in her pain-filled nightmares was she reaching for? The Ranger---OR---something else??<br><br>Earlier, seeing Azzarria rushing back to her camp, throwing provisions and clothing into her pack--Noticed, the look of abject fear written on those lovely features! Alarms went off within him!!<br>What has happened to make her act thus?? Gathering quickly, items of travel, he followed her through their tunnels.<br>At one point, he had had to stop at a nearby hut for an item he had forgotten...Thus losing her!!! Pure luck alone...He thought...found him near her once more!!<br><br>Nodding off himself, put his pipe to bed, gathering his woolen clock tighter about. -- Knowing in his Love Lost Soul..Either behind her OR beside her, Brylin had to find the answer to the burning question, of what would make this hardened beastlord leave the protection of his glade!**<br><br>Darrien, gathering abundant supplies, knows it will be some time before he can look upon the beauty of Surefall once more. Embracing both his parents, Darrien says - &quot;&quot;If it be in my Rangers power - I will return with Azzarria.&quot;<br>&quot;Guard yourself well, my son,&quot; &quot;Gorr and his gathering minions, are not to be taken lightly!!&quot; &quot;The truth is now known..You and the Beastlord have high prices on your heads!!&quot;<br><br>Nodding his understanding of these words, Darrien takes leave of the glade. When reaching the outer passages, he hesitates. &quot;Would Azzarria of gone to her people for help??&quot; Shaking his head, he knows this not to be true! Even though his love is running blindly towards her future...she would never tolerate harm to those she loves!!<br><br>Gathering his thoughts once more - Ranger Instincts, bury deep his Elven feelings!<br>Pushing onward, Darrien reaching the Crossroads -- hesitates. Something is not right here! Tracking messages flash-fire in his mind!! &quot;What is this??&quot; &quot;I feel strongly her presence..yet something else lingers here also!!&quot;<br><br>Knowing it to be too soon for Gorr's Army to reach here, confusion sets in. Is she being followed?? By whom or what??<br><br>Following Azzarria's scent on the winds.....It seems to be everywhere, yet no-where!! Did she travel to Qeynos? Whom does she know there abouts?<br><br>Urgency pushing his tracking talents to their limits---&quot;Darrien&quot; makes a &quot;Fatal Judgement&quot;!!! If..Only he had continued down the path he had been on!!!<br><br>Hoping against all hope, Darrien rushes to Qeynos, hoping to find his beloved, being attended by their local healer and safe from harm.<br><br><br>Part 8..........To be continued.<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Azzarria - "Stormchild"<br>"The Huntress"</td></tr>
