	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189461><span id=Sage>Taimarawee</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>**In a cold sweat, Azzarria-tossing back her blankets-comes fully awake!!<br><br>Some form of warning is pressing onto her, but she does not understand!<br><br>Walking silently, as not to disturb Brylin, goes over to check on the Druid. Realizing that the feeling is not coming from him..looks to the heavens for guidence.<br>By the Gods!!! What is going on with ME?!? <br><br>Brylin seeming to sense her presence, even in his pain-wracked dreams--bringing Azzarria out of her troubled thoughts.<br>Quickly gathering &amp; making a fresh herbal healing brew--has to force Brylin still, so that he will drink it!<br><br>Her mind now fully on Brylin..neglects any further nagging feelings within!<br><br>**Darrien feels a cool, soothing hand upon his forehead caressing his sweaty brow.<br>Opening his one good eye, a vision of arcane beauty swims to view.<br>Trying to rise - he is pushed gently back down. &quot;Hush now Ranger&quot;, the silken voice says. &quot;Be still, while I check the vastness of your wounds!&quot; &quot;It looks to me you are badly hurt!!&quot;<br><br>A wounded sigh escapes Darrien's lips, as she touches and pokes hither and yon.<br>&quot;WOMAN!&quot; &quot;PLEASE!&quot; &quot;I can not take this much longer!!&quot;<br><br>A gentle smile escapes him from this Dark-Skinned beauty, as she stills beside him.<br>&quot;I see, even though badly hurt, you are fiesty still!!&quot;<br><br>Helping Darrien to somewhat sit-up and lean him to the mossy wall - asks his name.<br>&quot;Begging your forgiveness, Lady!&quot; &quot;The pain has me not myself!!&quot;<br>&quot;My name is &quot;Darrien Lockard&quot; - &quot;I hail near here, from Surefall Glade.&quot; &quot;May I, in return ask for yours?&quot;<br><br>&quot;SHE&quot;--hesitates!! Darrien's brows come together in a frown! <br>&quot;Be YOU my enemy - fair Lady??&quot;<br><br>&quot;NO!&quot; - &quot;NO-O Ranger...ah Darrien!&quot; &quot;It has jus been a long while, whence anyone cared to know it!!&quot;<br>&quot;My name is..&quot;Chaz'et Da`Linn&quot; - &quot;I come from Neriak.&quot;<br><br>Nodding to himself, Darrien knows this to be true, by her Dark Skin, Silken Silver hair, and her radiating beauty known to the Tier'dal heritage.<br><br>&quot;Now, that-that is out of the way&quot;, she laughs - &quot;I, with your permission would like to help you!&quot; &quot;After though, I would like to know how you came to be in this diseased place of torment!!&quot; Nodding his head..she proceeds.<br><br>Laying her graceful fingers upon his hot bare chest, calls forth her magiks.<br>Darrien begins to feel a burning sensation within and howls with pain!!<br>&quot;Be still love!&quot; &quot;It will go away shortly!&quot; &quot;Tis only a healing spell--I Promise!&quot;<br>Gasping for air, he can not reach, falls towards her unconscious!<br><br>**As days turn the clock of time forward-Darrien still has not returned to her!!<br>Sensing great evil, &quot;Chaz'et knows WHAT is beside her!!<br><br>&quot;Death&quot; hovers near him, waiting--waiting impatiently for that weak moment, to take this ONE into it's fold!!<br><br>&quot;Chaz'et will have none of this!! She will fight with everything she possesses to win this one!!<br>&quot;This Ranger is mine NOW!&quot; &quot;YOU will NOT have HIM!!&quot; &quot;Begone with YOU - &quot;Angel of Death!!&quot;<br><br>&quot;Death&quot; seems not to want to comply to her wishes! &quot;You are also a &quot;DEATH DEALER&quot; Necromancer!!&quot; &quot;Why your interest in this one??&quot;<br><br>Shimmering Violet eyes stare him down!! Never wavering, lest she fail her bluff to this Dark Beast &quot;SHE&quot; answers: &quot;I found him!!&quot; &quot;I desire HIM--BE GONE from my presence!!!&quot;<br><br>Throwing back his massive horned head, roars with laughter!!<br>&quot;Chaz'et&quot; has had about ENOUGH of this!!! Deep anger comes unbridled onto to her!! She can NOT resist this nasty urge within her being!!<br>Razor sharp rays of irresistible white-hot light, flash out from her fingers, striking &quot;Death&quot;---Straight to its blackened heart---Picking him up and slamming him against the granite wall!!!<br><br>Fetid smelling blood surfaces on his scaley body, causing his eyes to bulge with shock!!!!<br>&quot;This CAN NOT BE, for &quot;I&quot; am &quot;The Deathbringer!!&quot; &quot;ALL are humbled in my presence-'No One' has YET to bring me down!!&quot;<br><br>Gliding forward--A vicious laugh erupts from the Necromancer! Grabbing the weakened beast says: &quot;AS AM-&quot;I&quot;-BEAST!!!&quot;<br><br>In its long undulating existance, never has Fear resided in that blackened soul, till NOW!<br>Narrowing those yellow-slitted eyes, bows to her. &quot;As you wish Necromancer!&quot; &quot;Be aware though&quot; - &quot;In doing this, YOU have sealed your fate and those around you to ME in the here-after!!&quot;<br>Jerking free of her, Death vanishes, leaving a rancid stench behind.<br><br>Weakened greatly..The beautiful Necromancer shudders, trying to regain her self being!<br>&quot;SHE&quot; unlike her kind - has a good heart! This came not from her Tier'dal heritage, but from a kindly human Warrior, who took her under his wing when she was in her tender seasons.<br><br>**Never could she understand her people! Their ways of constant death and destruction to the world outside their own.<br>A gleam comes to her eyes, as she remembers the grief she caused her house - Constantly! Always asking, always prying for answers to Tier'dal ways!<br>Chaz'et could not help it - she was born to Nobility and saw the hardships and strife laid upon the lesser people of her home. <br><br>In voicing these opinions one too many times, had her best friend &quot;Iaaki&quot; sending her a note: &quot;To leave quickly and as quietly as she could---For the &quot;House Da`Linn&quot; had put out a &quot;Death Warrant&quot; on her!<br><br>Late at night, when Chaz'et would finally stop, out of pure exhaustion--would Grief, Pain and Humilation catch up with her. She really did love her people, regardless of their culture. NEVER did she think that it would go as far as it had!!!<br><br>Scared, Lost and Wandering alone in the savage area of East Commons is where her Adopted Father found her.<br><br>Shaking herself from those horrid memories, looks to her Ranger Darrien. I still need to find out why he was in such great peril in the Sewers of Qeynos!!<br>&quot;My Gods!&quot; &quot;How hurt he was!&quot;--&quot;Still is for that matter!&quot; &quot;I am NOT sure, I HAVE won the fight with Death--'YET'!&quot;<br><br>Not being able to help herself, she had found and read the parchment that he carried.<br>Sparks of Fury shown in those strange Violet eyes of hers!!! Chaz'et knew in her long travels, that Rangers were of good ilk!! The killing had to of been with good reason!<br>No judgement from her! Besides! What did it matter? She held NO alligence to their kind!! The only reason she had been there, was to find an elusive ingredient, needed for her work.<br><br>Eyes drifting once more to Darrien, her fury would not abate!!! &quot;I&quot; think when this is finished--&quot;I&quot; will pay a nice visit back there and have me some fun with these &quot;Bloodsabers!!&quot;<br><br>Chaz'et finding help of &quot;Kind&quot;--Had Darrien transported to &quot;SharVahl&quot;. Knowing this beautiful city held no hate of them. Now she could concentrate on matters at hand. Hoping against all hope, with her abilities, he would heal!!<br><br>Stiffly rising from sitting too long, once more lays her soft hands upon Darriens fevered chest, releasing waves of Magenta Mist over him. Finishing up her work, fatigue has now overcome this skilled Necromancer!<br>Curling up beside Darrien to protect him from - what may - looks to the candle-lit cozy room, smiling to herself, as she drifts to her sleep.<br><br>Part 11......To Be Continued<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Azzarria - "Stormchild"<br>"The Huntress"</td></tr>
