	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189461><span id=Sage>Taimarawee</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Darrien, trying to get his fury under control, notices a small pristine pond near the Monk's guild. It's soothing water calls to him. Sitting near the small pond..Darrien takes &quot;Shal'ette&quot; lovingly out of his sheath and starts to clean her.<br>This sword was given to him by Drinel, upon accomplishing the shaman tasks he had given him over his younger seasons. Once..NO Twice Darrien had almost failed his teacher! Drinel though, having a soft place in his heart for his young Ranger apprentice...Patiently continued on with him until he had learned truly the Art.<br>How he loved this sword! Her Silvered lines-straight and pure. Her glistening edges, honed to a razor sharpness.--If touched-could instantly cut to the Bone!<br>Deep engravings near the hilt were etched with pure Gold. Symbols of power for only he to understand.<br><br>Finishing this, Darrien looks up and sees, &quot;The Crows Nest&quot;. A tavern known for its seedy patrons and dark doings. He had heard of this tavern and knew he should not enter, knowing of the dangers that could lie within for him.<br>&quot;I must!&quot; &quot;I have to know if the merchant was correct in his telling, or NO!!<br><br>Stepping into the &quot;Crows Nest&quot;, he closes the warped wooden door carefully. The screeching hinges protesting its closure.<br>Eyes, slowly adjusting to the dim, smoke laden tavern--Hails an Ale' from the passing tavern wench.<br>Seeing in the distant corner a beer-stained table, decides that one will do for listening to conversations going on. <br><br>As he is waiting for his Ale'.. Darrien realizes how weary he has become. Wiping dirt and grime from the road off his handsome face--closes his tired eyes and leans back against the roughened wall for a brief respite.<br><br>Slamming-his mug of Ale' down..the tavern wench bends to him and says: &quot;You have NO business here Ranger!--Drink up and be gone..Whilst you can!!&quot;<br>&quot;Mind Yer Duties, wench...Leave mine to ME!!&quot;<br>Taking a long pull of his cold Ale'..Notices a bitter taste to the brew!! -- Shrugs thinking it to be only a dirty mug.<br><br>*******It is done! Unknown to Darrien,--A deadly, yet not killing potion, is now threading itself through-out him!<br><br>A conversation takes his interest! Leaning closer, to the tables edge, he hears two shadowknights complaining of their treatment by one-&quot;Scragg Bloodheart&quot;. The one most injured, is ready for a fight!<br>At yet another table..A drunken Cleric laughs, throwing her long dirty hair back. Saying: over-boastful of her talents!--&quot;Who can compete with her Gods of Disease-OR-of her magiks!&quot;<br><br>Having heard ENOUGH!..Darrien sets his mug to the table. As he stands, his sight wavers. &quot;What is this?&quot; Shaking his head to clear it, makes his way to the Cleric.<br><br>&quot;YOU boast yer skills, woman!!&quot; &quot;Have you, in your insane dealings within the sewers, harmed or healed a Beastlord these days past?!&quot;<br><br><br>A Pall-so thick, you could slice it with a dagger, falls over the tavern!<br><br>The Cleric stands--As she turns, Darrien's nostrils are filled with her unwashed body stench!<br>&quot;Well, well..Lookie here!&quot; &quot;A Glade Ranger!&quot; &quot;Lost are we!?&quot;, she snears.<br>&quot;Even if I knew or did this deed you speak of--&quot;I&quot; most certainly would NOT share my fun of it with YOU!!!&quot;<br><br>Hatred for this loathsome creature slowly rises within Darrien, choking him with its bile!<br>Stepping back, Darrien draws &quot;Shal'ette&quot;, running her through to the hilt!!<br>Grasping hold of Darrien's sword, the cleric slowly sinks to the wooden floor..sticky blood pooling beneath her!<br><br><br>Ungodly silence fills the tavern, suffocating the Patrons around him!!<br>Then!!--Chairs slam back-breaking! Tables overturn, beer and spirits, overpowering the dusky air!! Tavern Patrons, breaking the door to get out!!!<br><br>Through a dim head pounding mist Darrien realizes his mistake!! &quot;What have I done?&quot;<br>&quot;Why do I feel so strange?&quot;***The drug is working its deadly crawl within him.**<br><br>Sheathing &quot;Shal'ette&quot;, his knees start to buckle! Grabbing the rickity table for balance, breathes deep and turns around to the men.<br><br>&quot;This was NOT your fight&quot;--&quot;Leave it BE!!&quot;<br><br>The more bloodied of the two shadownights, chuckles a deep, evil sound within his chest! Two giant strides he is upon Darrien, grabbing him by the throat and squeezing his life air out of him, raising him off the floor!!<br>Lacking breathe, Darrien's vision blurs, black spots dancing before his eyes!<br>Rasping--through an almost closed air passage says: &quot;Release ME!&quot;--OR--Your Gods will be seeing you sooner than THEY even expected!!!&quot;<br><br>Almost instantly, the hand is removed from around his throat! Darrien falls to the floor, pain following! Before Darrien can take a cleansing breathe--something heavy slams into the side of his head!!<br>Life-blood flowing freely down his neck--Velvet darkness decends on this Ranger!! As he slips away to unknown planes..his last thoughts are of a beautiful barbarian beastlord.<br><br><br>***An infectious Shadow of Insipid Blackness floats silently down a dank moss-covered passage. It senses a living thing ahead!<br>Following some dark evil instinct, it homes in on its Prey!!<br><br>There!!<br><br>Ahead!!<br><br>It pulsates and quivers, watching this living thing, moan and toss. &quot;YES&quot;!! &quot;It still breathes!!&quot;<br>Alas though...It is being summoned from another direction! Frustrated-It has to follow the commanding summons! It can not RESIST! It Dare NOT!! It's Master is far more powerful than the Shadow!!<br>Sadly, it turns back the way it had traveled--remembering the area of this &quot;Living Thing&quot;, so that it may return--&quot;To PLAY with it!!&quot;***<br><br><br>Consciousness--Then blinding, white-hot pain, brings Darrien from his depths of Hell! His sight almost gone, he slowly rises to his knees, taking in his surroundings!<br>From long battles, instinct makes him reach for &quot;Shal'ette&quot;, but she is NOT with him!!! Nor are any of his other weapons and Bow!<br>Needing to quench his raging thirst, he reaches also for his water. --- They have stripped him of everything!!! No weapons, no provisions, nor are his healing herbs on him!!!<br><br>Trying to once again stand, Darrien feels an item within his cloak. Blindly reaches within its folds, pulls out a smelly, badly-stained piece of parchment. On it is written:<br><br>**&quot;Our &quot;People&quot; Do NOT take kindly to the killings of one of our own!&quot;<br>We gathered information of you wanting to know of the sewers and a certain beastlord, possibly being down here.<br>We have respected yer wishes.<br>&quot;Make yerself comfortable Glade Ranger, for you will be here a LONG while!<br>Regards,<br>The &quot;Bloodsabers&quot;<br>Ha-ha-ha-ha-ha!!--Enjoy yer stay!!<br>***<br><br>His mind shuts down!! A wetness begins in his green eyes, he can not control! Tears sliding down that rugged face, that has seen so much death! Now, possibly--It has become his turn!<br><br>Raising that badly beaten proud head of his...His ragged thoughts, call upon the winds of fortune, to send forth a message to his beastlord.<br><br>&quot;Azzarria&quot; my beating heart is slowing. Know this my beautiful lady! My love for you will carry me to my end, come what may!!!<br><br>No longer able to kneel..Darrien sinks to the level of the clammy earth and crawls to what he hopes is a safe haven for the time--to Hide.<br><br>Part 10....to be continued<br>&quot;Azzarria&quot;<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jun 19 16:49:46 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Azzarria - "Stormchild"<br>"The Huntress"</td></tr>
