	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189461><span id=Sage>Taimarawee</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Brylin, not being able to contain himself any longer--Leaps down from the Wyntertree.<br>Shifting, he becomes his Alter Self.<br><br>Stretching, back curved, tail high...He is Beautiful to gaze upon! Silvery Blue-Grey coat stirring, as the warm winds play havoc and dance within his long fur!<br>Slowly..He approaches the sleeping beastlord-moist nose upraised to the shifting summer winds, he breathes in deeply of Azzarria's scent!<br><br>Human urges and wanting for her, almost make him lose control of his magnificent wolf-form!<br>Backing further away--sits, watching her toss in her sleep.<br><br>Drawing upon his Druid ability, cast the Magik across the way.<br>Warm Colbalt-Blue Rays shoot across and engulf the Ailing Beastlord!<br>Azzarria--No the Wiser, for the time, sleeps more deeply now. Less troubled than before!<br>Nodding to himself..A wolfen grin appears upon those Killing Jaws.<br><br>Brylin pads away, looking for a stream to quench his thirst and something to Hunt!<br>Keen night Eyes, see in the distance--&quot;Prey!&quot; A mangy werewolf loping across the plains!!<br><br>&quot;A little Off-Course, are we..&quot;ScumDogg??&quot;<br>This is Exactly the fight Brylin is looking for to tamper his Hungry Feelings of Desire, he knows he shouldn't have!!!<br><br>His mind No Longer Human, the Druid Wolf targets in on his find...Heavy Muscles quiver and tighten for the Kill!!!<br>Leaping forward--ground and distance being swallowed--within seconds Brylin hits hard the Werewolf, knocking him to the hard packed earth!!<br>Massive Jaws reach for NECK, snapping closed on....&quot;AIR!!&quot;--- &quot;WHAT??&quot;<br>Pains screams its release down his side!! The Werewolf had sensed his comings! <br>Curved talons for maiming once more slit Brylin's side open, making Brylin almost go blind with his rage and pain!!!<br><br>Turning, he slips in his own Blood, but rights himself in time to run full force into the werewolf, using his shoulder to uplift the hell hound...exposing the sensitive middle!<br>Weakened, seeing nothing but Blood Red...Brylin's jaws rip open the middle, tearing out vital organs!!<br><br>Raising its head, the werewolf screams to the night!!! To Kin, that will No MORE run with him--Collapses--Pinning Brylin to the ground, almost crushing him with its massive dead weight!!<br><br>**The Plain is Now Hushed**<br>Nothing Moves-Creatures of Awesome Power have been halted in their tracks!! Trying to shake the terrifying screams from their minds..that have occured this very night!!<br><br>Crawling and Scratching, inch by pain-wracked inch, the maimed Druid Wolf finds his way out from under the dead creature.<br>So badly injured is he..Brylin loses shape..Becoming once more the Human.<br>Trying desperately to rise, knowing his loss of blood is great..Too Late! Blackness slams into him...he falls once more to the cold ground!!<br><br>Smelling the Rich, Coppery odor of Warm Blood, a Griffin, floating with the currents, edges closer!<br><br>Darrien, having reached NorthQeynos, starts his inquiry into Azzarria's possible where-abouts.<br>One such merchant...having a great dislike for Darrien and his family-Dupes Him!<br>&quot;The Fool Girl has gone into our Sewers!&quot; &quot;That CAN NOT be merchant!&quot; &quot;She would never go Below!&quot;<br>&quot;Believe what you will Ranger,&quot; says the merchant--&quot;This is what I have been told!&quot;--&quot;That a passing Beastlord was here, looking of help for her cause, and a quick remedy for her ills!!&quot;<br>Looking intently at this man, Darrien shakes his head. &quot;I still Do Not believe you.&quot; &quot;Since time is now my enemy, count yourself lucky, to still be in One Piece for saying this!!&quot;<br>Stalking out and slamming the door, Darrien with fear gripping his heart, hopes what he was just told is NOT to be true!<br><br>Dawn comes, bringing Azzarria out of a deep sleep, she has not experienced in quite some time. Throwing off her blankets..Azzarria is hit with cold, clammy fingers of Daybreak crawling across silken skin!<br>Brrrrrr!! Hugging herself, she finds her tunic and slips it on!<br><br>For some reason, yet unknown, the beastlord does not feel the need to rush, nor yet leave the valley. Humming a toon she learned as a child, Azzarria finds drywood for her campfire. Waiting for breakfast to be done, Azzarria tries to remember where she had seen that stream late the night last.<br>Finally!!<br>The Stream!!<br>Jumping into it full force, brings her rising to the top, gasping for air from the chilled water! Breath restored...she floats momentarily on its water, remembering her Lake swims, listening to the waters of her beloved land. A Special place..I must say!!<br><br>Enough!!!<br>Rising from the Stream--she is a sight to behold indeed!!! Full-figured, heavily muscled from years of fighting...She yet still retains the soft alluring curves of a young girl!!! Throwing her long Auburn hair back..sends water spraying in all directions at once! Gods...that bath felt good!!!<br><br>I am different this morning!!<br>My fever is almost dimished, my aches are few-AND- I was humming a tune my father taught me the years ago!!<br>This should NOT be...My Ills were many-My Hurts Great!<br>Seasoned as she was, she knew that neither Fate nor Luck has anything to do with this.<br><br>Climbing the shallow bank, Azzarria comes to see Wolf tracks, of unusual size. Questions start to arise, but alas--so does her hunger!<br><br>Seeing nothing on the horizons that appear to threaten her, she continues on back to camp to relish the sweet smelling porriage bubbling away in her blackened pot.<br>As Azzarria is enjoying this feast, she begins to feel gentle touchings around her soul.<br>Sitting down her bowl, she carefully calls forth to her beloved Pet-PonPi'. Almost at once he is..once more..before her!!!<br><br>Kneeling down, Azzarria grabs Ponpi', nearly crushing him with her Joy!!!<br>Good natured Ponpi' growls at her for his release! Dashing glistening tears from her eyes...Azzarria tries hard to collect herself, letting Ponpi' from her bear-hugging grip!!<br><br>All this is just TOO much for this poor beastlord!! Needing to sit back down to take this all in....Assumes, her soft blanketed seat is still beneath her--SITS!<br><br>Missing it entirely, hitting the hard ground with a whumpp--bringing shooting pains to that pretty backside of hers!!!!<br>&quot;NOW!&quot; &quot;See what you have done, my pet??&quot;<br>Blinking away tears of minor pain-- brushes off various burrs, stuck to such a lovely area!<br>Ponpi'..tilting his wolfen head to one side, gives a Puppy Dog Grin and wanders away to drink from the stream.<br><br>Much wool-gathering later---Rested, contented and re-united with her beloved Pet, Azzarria decided to stay this quaint valley for another day.<br>Once again, humming that child-hood tune, she begins to tidy up their campsite.<br><br>Ponpi' begins a mournful howl--jerking Azzarria from her carefree thoughts! She can hear him, but she doesn't see him! &quot;What in Tar-Nashon is going on with that Wolf??&quot;<br>Finding his tracks crossing-over the larger wolf tracks, starts to sort out the two to follow.<br>In the distance, there Ponpi' is.. standing guard over something! Calling to him, he won't give ground! Puzzling this-Azzarria, throwing her hands in the air, decides to see what &quot;PRIZE&quot; Ponpi' wants to give her!<br>Mumbling and knowing his interesting hunting habits..can just imagine what it will be!!<br><br>Getting closer...she halts--There is a foul smell of Blood on the air! Too much stench, to be one of Ponpi's small hunting kills!<br>Running now, she comes upon a very gruesome sight! Before her on the ground is a badly injured man...she thinks!! Blood and Gore are everywhere! Near him is a vile werewolf--dead, thank the gods!!<br>Looking to the South, sees a Griffon with something that looks like an arm or leg clutched in its claw!<br>Nausea setting in, Azzarria is almost afraid to look any closer at this man!<br>Steeling her feelings of revulsion and fear, pushes Ponpi' out of the way to take a look.<br><br>His Gods, seemed to of stayed with him in his fight. Everything is where it should be--Blood loss is great, but stitching quickly will end that problem! Bending near his chest, she hears his heart beating slow, but strong.<br>Standing back up Azzarria starts scouting for the makings to carry this poor soul back to her camp.<br><br>Looking to Ponpi...she already knows the answer she is asking of this wolf...he will help her carry him back.<br><br>OH! This poor injured being!!--I try to be gentle while cleaning and stitching! He moans..starting to thrash when I sew close his wounds!! I know, I have hurt him more! ...It can Not be helped!!<br>Ponpi' looks on and growls softly my way, when hearing him moan! Frustrated, I throw a look his way--begging him to understand what I am doing, must BE Done!!<br><br>As my Warm Summer Sun, melts into the lands, it is finally finished!!! I have done what I could...pray, that be Enough!!<br>Wrapping his clock and my blankets around him to guard the chill, I call to Ponpi' to walk with me for a time.<br>He refuses...&quot;Aye Pup!&quot;---&quot;Like the man, do you??&quot;<br><br>Although exhausted, I know I still have work to do for him. Gathering herbs I find on the ground...I boil them out. Knowing in my heart...he is NOT going to like the Taste of what I have just made!<br>Kneeling closely, I coax him to take small amounts of this brew, whispering to him all the while, that it will help and heal.<br>Thinking, I have finally got enough down him to help--I gaze more closely at this man.<br><br>Listening to his steady even breathing, I realize how handsome he is! After getting the blood and gore off of him, he ..YES--Is quite handsome!<br>My eyes travel the length of him, seeing a body that, although ravished...is quite muscled and toned.<br>MY GOD!! Azzarria!!! What is wrong with you??? This man was near-death and YOU are having Thoughts??!!<br><br>Bowing my head, shame travels over me!!<br>I feel a soft feather-like touch to my face, forcing me to look at him.<br>Smiling at me, he refuses to let me go! His hand travels to my hair...entwining his fingers in it..he pulls me closer, whispering, &quot;Azzarria&quot;-&quot;You know naught, how I've longed for this moment!&quot;<br><br>Thinking him to be addled with too much of my herbed-drink, I gently try to pull away.<br>What is your name? Where do you hail from friend?<br>Taking a not too steady breathe says, &quot;My name beautiful lady is &quot;Brylin&quot;--&quot;I hail from &quot;The Glades.&quot; &quot;I am a Druid in residence there.&quot;<br><br>Shaking my head--&quot;Nay,&quot; &quot;I have not seen you there!&quot;<br>&quot;OH!!&quot; &quot;I was there, when they brought you in M'Lady&quot;--&quot;Believe you me&quot;--&quot;I was t-theree seeing Y-YOU!&quot;<br><br>Quickly..checking him, I realize he has only collasped once more into his darkness.<br><br>Tucking him in once more--I gather Ponpi', to sit to the edge of the fire and absorb this. Random thoughts rush through my mind! This Druid--&quot;Brylin&quot;...I must find out more of him and the meanings to his tellings to me!!<br><br>Nestling closer still--to Ponpi'--Azzarria falls into her own exhausted sleep.<br>What now..will you dream of Sweet Lady??<br><br>To be cont....Part 9 <br>Azzarria<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Azzarria - "Stormchild"<br>"The Huntress"</td></tr>
