	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189461><span id=Sage>Taimarawee</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Upon awakening, Azzarria is hit with a sensation of &quot;Death&quot; knocking on her door!<br>Not quite understanding this foreboding feeling, she goes looking for Darrien for comfort.<br><br>Coming upon Darrien - Finds him deep in conversation with his father Samuel and the Elders of Surefall. Backing away, Azzarria, not meaning to evesdrop, does so without thinking.<br><br>&quot;We&quot; have had wind of trouble coming to our lands,&quot; says Samuel. &quot;By this, meaning what Father?&quot;<br>&quot;One of my runners was delivering a message from I, to &quot;Ikthar&quot;, in East Freeport.<br><br>Knowing he shouldn't, but parched from his long journey, went into the &quot;Seafarer's Roost&quot; for a quick drink. Sitting, silently in a dimly lit corner, he heard this being said from a passing Rogue.<br><br>&quot;Gorr&quot; in their neighboring Desert is putting a Bounty on &quot;You&quot; -- Darrien and Azzarria's head!<br>&quot;In telling&quot; - this Giant &quot;Gorr&quot; is without end!!! &quot;Gorr&quot; will stop at nothing less than your death's for the killing of his brother, &quot;Lorr&quot;!! As I speak, I am told that he has amassed enemies of ours by his side, to find Azzarria!&quot; &quot;SHE&quot;, &quot;above ALL he looks for!!!&quot;<br><br>Gasping!..Azzarria, backs deeper into the shadows. &quot;I&quot; can not let this go on!&quot; &quot;I&quot;, must leave this tranquil Village!&quot;<br>Burning Darrien's handsome face into her memory, Azzarria slips away to pack.<br><br>It matters &quot;NOT&quot; to this Beastlord, that her body is weakened - NOR that she still can not summon her Ponpi'! What &quot;DOES&quot; matter is, getting away from Surefall, before disaster strikes these kind and generous people she loves!<br>Packing quickly, Azzarria departs through the tunnels.<br><br>Blinking against the early morning glare - Azzarria - Once more, must fight another fight!....&quot;TO THE DEATH!&quot;.....Little does she know, how Much Stronger and Full of Hate THIS Brother IS!!!!!<br><br>Back at the Elder's Campfire, Darrien tries to control the rising temperment of his Father and Elders....&quot;I&quot;, will go to Freeport to see if what we are hearing is of &quot;Truth Spoken&quot; - or Tales from a Drunken Rogue!&quot;<br>&quot;Ayes&quot; are spoken on this decision, pacifying concerns for the moment.<br><br>Knowing this is serious, but maybe &quot;Ale Spoken&quot;, goes to find his beloved.<br><br>Darrien's eyes see more than they should!! Azzarria's camp has been turned asunder! &quot;By My Gods!!&quot; &quot;Where has she gone??&quot;<br>Running quickly across his village - he asks of her where-abouts.<br>&quot;Ranger&quot;...&quot;She be gone!&quot; &quot;On Brother Suns Arising, I saw her traveling thru our passages!&quot;<br><br>Panic choking Darrien...Knowing of her injuries, races to his Fathers side!<br>&quot;Father&quot;...&quot;I must leave, NOW! &quot;Azzarria, must of caught wind of our conversations, and has left the Glade!!!&quot;<br><br>Samuel's love of this Girl.........Has Blood draining from his face! Nodding to his son - &quot;Go quickly Darrien&quot;, &quot;she will NOT win that fight!&quot; &quot;Gorr&quot; will most certainly KILL her!!!&quot;<br><br>Tracking Instincts racing thru him, he sets out to find this Foolish Beastlord of his!!<br><br>****Will he find her in TIME??? &quot;If I lose her...I lose All Meaning to My Life!!&quot;<br><br>Part 7........To be continued</p>&nbsp;<br>Azzarria - "Stormchild"<br>"The Huntress"</td></tr>
