	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=105234662511670>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=105234662511670>"Gorr"  #6</a> <a id=fs8 href=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=105234662511670#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, May 7th 7:10 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189461><span id=Sage>Taimarawee</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&quot;Gorr&quot; looks to his dead brother - Pain &amp; Humiliation residing deep in his massive chest. Standing - &quot;Gorr&quot; tightens his massive fists!!! Within him - &quot;Everything Has DIED!&quot;<br><br>Bellowing to his 2nd in Command &quot;Tallis&quot; to follow him...his long strides carry him back to the encampment once more.<br><br>Winded &amp; finally having caught up with his Lord, &quot;Tallis&quot; hesitates.---He has never seen this &quot;Look of Death&quot;, that is now etched on &quot;Gorrs&quot; face! &quot;My Lord&quot; - What do you require of me?&quot; Like a snake, &quot;Gorr&quot; strikes, digging deeply into Tallis' throat!! &quot;Where were YOU for my BROTHER!!&quot; &quot;You were on patrol with him!!!&quot; Vice-like fingers of steel had Tallis gasping for air!!<br><br>&quot;Please....My L-Lord, let me tell you what happened!!&quot; &quot;Gorr&quot;, releasing his strangle-hold, steps back...&quot;EXPLAIN!&quot; or &quot;YOU DIE..NOW!&quot; Dragging deep, hurtful breaths, Tallis begins.<br><br>&quot;Lorr&quot; &amp; &quot;I&quot; were on patrol in the SouthEast corner of our lands, having heard activity of our enemy - The Human Scum of Freeport - traveling through our lands.&quot; &quot;True to the report, we were ambushed by Warriors, near the bottom of &quot;Hags Dune&quot;. &quot;I took a massive blow from behind, losing thought for mere moments..I assure you my Lord!!&quot;<br>Narrowing Yellow-encrusted eyes--&quot;Gorr&quot; ROARS!!! &quot;WAIT!..My Lord!!&quot; When my thoughts cleared, broken corpses lay scattered around me.&quot;....&quot;Lorr&quot;, no where to be seen, only his tracks leading South. Following them, the winds bring me sounds of furious battle!&quot; &quot;Running faster, I crest a Dune.&quot; &quot;In the distance, I see &quot;Lorr&quot; fighting a female Barbarian Beastlord, with a wolf-like creature by her side.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Tallis&quot; pauses--knowing what next he tells, could be the last breath he will ever draw! &quot;My Lord&quot;, &quot;This Beastlord was gaining the Fight!!&quot; -- &quot;Flashing silver weapons of two, her creature wolf throwing Bolts of Lightening!!&quot; &quot;Magiks, I have never seen!&quot; &quot;Lorr&quot;, WAS losing ground and BLOOD!&quot; Quickly...&quot;Tallis&quot; continues, seeing &quot;Gorr&quot; move towards him!<br><br>&quot;Then&quot;...&quot;Lorr&quot; did something that I had forgotten you had taught him in battle.&quot; &quot;Feigning far greater injury than he had, he went down on one knee and bowed before the Beastlord, stopping the fight!!!!&quot; &quot;The female halted in mid swing.&quot; &quot;I could see confusion upon her face!&quot; &quot;Lorr&quot; sensing his Victory, rose and Bashed her!&quot; &quot;Reeling , she fell back.&quot; &quot;I know &quot;Lorr&quot; had WON!!!&quot; He would have her roasted for his meal this very eve!!&quot;<br><br>&quot;Blinking against the glare off the Dune, I see a Ranger at her side!&quot; &quot;Lord Gorr&quot;, &quot;I&quot; swear onto you...He just APPEARED, as if by Magik means!!&quot; &quot;I saw his Bow draw taught--The Arrow's Aim was true--Your Brother Died at their FEET!&quot;<br><br>&quot;NOOO!&quot; roared &quot;Gorr&quot; -- &quot;I WILL HAVE THEIR HEADS FOR THIS!!!!!&quot; Enraged, &quot;Gorr&quot; swung, hitting &quot;Tallis&quot; and breaking his neck with the blow!<br><br>Silence reigned heavily on his camp. Not a &quot;Sand Giant&quot; moved, for fear of what &quot;Gorr&quot; would do next!<br>Seconds turned to minutes--Minutes seemed like hours to these towering Giants! Finally, gaining control of his rage, he turns.....&quot;Break Camp&quot; &quot;NOW!!&quot; &quot;We are to travel this night.&quot;<br><br>Walking apart from his people, &quot;Gorr&quot; falls heavily onto the sand. Pain, so deep for one of his kind, engulfing him. He could NOT show this side to his people! His kind was known for only pain and death if encountered!<br>Grabbing a wandering Lizard and feasting on it's flesh an idea comes upon him. He will find &quot;Dorn B`Dynn&quot;. Loathe he may be of this cutthroat Teir`Dal, he needed him to find out this Beastlords name and the Ranger fighting beside her!!!<br><br>Heading East, &quot;Gorr's&quot; simple mind is remembering where last he saw &quot;Dorn's&quot; Dervish companions. <br>There is a mystery surrounding &quot;Dorn B`Dynn&quot;. Rumors of &quot;Dorn&quot; being of the &quot;Indigo Brotherhood&quot;. &quot;Gorr&quot; would catch conversations on the winds, of Neriak, and &quot;Dorns&quot; association with it. One way or the other, it mattered little to this grieving Giant!<br><br>Thru the night they traveled...Upon first light of day &quot;Gorr&quot; sees the camp ahead. - Snatching a passing &quot;Orc&quot; - Throttling it within an inch of it's miserable life - Convinces it to go get &quot;Dorn&quot; from the encampment and bring him here.<br>Passing the time waiting, unsuspecting travelers meet dooms door from &quot;Gorr's Wrath&quot;.<br><br>A Hail arrives at the camp. Being under their Lords orders, this mysterious cutthroat, strides through unharmed.<br>&quot;What of me are you asking, Giant?&quot; &quot;Your kind Vile this Desert!&quot; &quot;Speak swiftly!!&quot; Ignoring the insult..&quot;Gorr&quot; tells &quot;Dorn&quot; of his brothers Death.<br>After hearing of this tale -- &quot;Dorn&quot; throws back his head and laughs! &quot;I&quot; know of whom you speak.&quot; &quot;I myself have fought her!!&quot; &quot;This Beastlord is a dangerous foe, Giant!!&quot; &quot;When I thought I had her soul..her Wolf almost was my Death!&quot; Leave her be &quot;Gorr&quot;...She will be the death of YOU also!&quot;<br><br>&quot;GIVE ME HER NAME CUTTHROAT&quot; or &quot;Your BLOOD will spill where you stand!!!&quot; Snearing, the &quot;Tier`Dal bowed - &quot;As you wish &quot;Gorr&quot;. The Beastlord's name is..&quot;Azzarria Zathla'een&quot;, she hails from &quot;Halas&quot;. &quot;I&quot; know naught of this Ranger you speak of.&quot; &quot;I&quot; suggest, if you find another unlucky &quot;Orc&quot; passing beneath your feet&quot; -- &quot;Send him to &quot;Ortallius&quot; in our neighboring Desert, he may know of this Ranger.&quot;<br><br>Grunting his thanks, &quot;Gorr&quot; burns the name of &quot;Azzarria&quot; into his brain, where it will fester the hate already rampaging there!!!<br><br>Making his way once more, back to his camp, plans are forming for the &quot;Destruction&quot; of an unsuspecting Beastlord!<br><br>&quot;Gorrs&quot; words of hate are carried in the breeze........&quot;Azzarria&quot;, &quot;Murderess of my Brother&quot;, &quot;Tread carefully!!&quot; Soon we shall meet!<br><br>***In her sleep...A Chill runs through Azzarria! Unknowing that her time of Peace &amp; Comfort in the Glades is about to END!!!<br><br>*****Part 6......To be Continued<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Azzarria - "Stormchild"<br>"The Huntress"</td></tr>
