	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=105234655511704>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=105234655511704>The Ranger & The Beastlord  #5</a> <a id=fs8 href=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=105234655511704#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, May 7th 7:09 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189461><span id=Sage>Taimarawee</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&quot;A Tale of Us&quot;<br><br>My senses alert - I smell and taste - the rich, deep, pungent odors of a Forest. &quot;A FOREST&quot;? &quot;Aye&quot;! &quot;Now I remember!&quot;. The Burning Sands of South Ro and the pain I inflicted on my Ranger!<br><br>Stretching, on the pine bows beneath me, I open my eyes. Amazement strikes when I behold the gargantuan trees rising high above me.<br>Forcing my mind to obey, I call for Ponpi'Kala for comfort.<br><br>Something has happened to me! I Can Not sense my companion! A strange loss settles. Tight bands of fear reach deep into me!<br>&quot;I&quot; - beastlord am not whole without Ponpi - he is in-part my soul!<br>Lying back crying...Is how my Ranger finds me.<br><br>Cupping my chin and gently raising my head, he says..&quot;Azzarria&quot; &quot;Do Not Fret So My Love&quot;. &quot;Your fight with &quot;Lorr&quot; hurt you more than even I knew&quot;. &quot;Time will heal yer head wound of this I am sure&quot;! <br>Ponpi is with you - he is in your very essence of being! Your Minds Strength however, has left you for now.<br>Let me..Now help you in Hunting and Companionship.<br><br>Hmmm....That word &quot;Companionship&quot;?! I wonder exactly what he means by this? First things first say I!!<br><br>Shyly, but with purpose I ask this one great question that has been preying ever so on my mind.<br>&quot;I know that you have been friends with my fathers Shaman for many seasons&quot;, but.. &quot;Why your love of me?&quot;<br>Abruptly..He looks at me, then a deep rich laugh erupts from him..sending shivers down my spine!<br>Bending down to where I lay, he pulls me to my feet..tossing that rich dark hair of his back off his shoulders.<br><br>I am so near him...I can think of nothing else right now. Mixtures of forest, wood smoke, leather and a new smell of JUST HIM assault my senses!!<br>Bending closer to me, he seeks my lips. By the Gods!! &quot;I can not help myself&quot;! I do want this man to kiss me!<br>Our lips meet..His - demanding even more of me...To open and experience him! Sensations I have never experienced before wash over me. My body and Knees grow weak!! Tighter he holds me still! Instinct of wanting him, has my hands reaching..reaching to inter-twine and wrap themselves around his neck and pull him closer still!!<br><br>**Time comes back to us...and we step apart. Calming my racing heartbeat once more...I look up at him. Smiling.. raising an eyebrow..I say: &quot;You still have not answered my question Ranger&quot;!!<br><br>Nodding, he draws me to a small cozy fire he has built and bids me sit near him.<br><br>&quot;Know this!&quot;...&quot;I have loved you, since I first set eyes on you many seasons ago in your village&quot;.<br>I used to watch your wild beauty, seeing you toss that Auburn hair and watch your crystal blue eyes flash...When you would Not get your way over certain things&quot;! &quot;Aye&quot;, my love, you took my breath away!!<br><br>**Here in lies the Tale of Us**<br><br><br>&quot;Stormchild&quot;, upon the wild and stormy nite of your Birth, you were destined for ME!<br>Our parents met by a rather un-foreseen incident!<br><br>**Lo'Rrin had decided to surprise Kahesha, by taking her away from the village and chores. Their travels took the couple to places Kahesha and sometimes..Lo'Rrin had never ventured to.<br><br>Seasons before your time, maps were scarce. Travelers..having to rely solely on the sun, moon and stars for guidence.<br>Lo'Rrin knowing of this, still did not care, for seeing his beloved wife's excitement was all that mattered to him.<br><br>One such journey took Lo'Rrin and Kahesha to the opening of my parents village..here in the Glades.<br>Lo'Rrin, not liking small dark confines, was reluctant to go forward. Kahesha laughing!!!...Called forth her companion &quot;DyPree&quot; - who always made her husband nervous to be around.<br><br>Several twists and turns later finally lead them to the opening of my village.<br>Stunned, by the quiet beauty of Surefall, your parents looked on, drinking in the towering trees, the waterfall and the quiet waters beneath, ever watching fish, waiting for that elusive insect to glide too closely to their waters.<br><br>Finally, Kahesha grabbed her husband and said: &quot;Let's explore and shop for a bit&quot;!<br>Shaking his head at his beautiful wife and giving DyPree a wide berth, followed.<br><br>Upon completion of provisions and a refreshing drink...Decided to have a small picnic near the falls. Kahesha noticed when setting up her small feast, an opening thru the falls! &quot;Oh Lo'Rrin&quot;! &quot;Come look at this&quot;...&quot;Let's go explore behind the Falls&quot;!!<br><br>A short swim later, had them at the hidden entrance. Pulling themselves up and drying off, they turned to look upon the sheer beauty of cascading water hiding this secret entrance.<br><br>All of a sudden there was an enormous roar and Kahesha felt a blow to her back! DyPree - Instantly attacking the bear, seeing his mistress in distress!<br><br>&quot;Gods Heavens&quot;!!! &quot;What is going on out there&quot;? Yelled my father Samuel. Running out the door and jestering for my mother Laah to keep me inside, went to find out what was happening in his village.<br><br>Following the sounds and roars from one of his bears, he swam across and up into the entrance behind the falls.<br>What a sight met his eyes!! Lo'Rrin trying to protect his wife! Kahesha trying to protect her companion! DyPree trying to protect everyone in general!!<br>Shutting his eyes for one brief moment and drawing a quick breath Samuel became part of the chaos!<br><br>Grabbing Lo'Rrin and Kahesha by their arms, he motioned for them to follow him back outside and to safety. Reluctant to let DyPree fight alone...Kahesha was finally convinced to follow the two men.<br>Finally reaching the other side and gaining their breath, Samuel asked for DyPree to be sent back to his plane. Kashesha complied and blessed silence once more reigned over the Glade.<br><br>Quickly, Samuel took your parents to our home to see how badly everyone was hurt.<br>Laah met everyone at the door, introductions went around and Kahesha was taken into the kitchen to have her wounds attended to.<br><br>Samuel, turning to your Father said..&quot;WHAT Were You Doing In the Cave&quot;!?? Lo'Rrin trying to regain some sense of himself, snapped back. &quot;WE WERE JUST LOOKING AT THE BRILLANT SHEET OF WATER CASCADING OVER THE CAVE'S ENTRANCE&quot;!!!!!<br>For some reason...I will never know, this struck my father as funny! That got Your Father laughing and our parents friendship was sealed!!<br><br>Sitting near the corner of our woodbox and watching all this...I was soon discovered by your parents.<br>&quot;OH&quot;! &quot;You have a son&quot;! &quot;What is his name&quot;? Proudly striding across the room, my father grabbed me and said: &quot;This is my first-born...&quot;Darrien&quot;!<br><br>During the meal that very evening it was decided that the couples would hunt for a time together and get to know better this land of ours.<br>Having decided this....Their adventures took them several places and experience and joy ran abundant!!!!<br><br>On the Eve of Lo'Rrin and Kahesha's parting, Lo'Rrin suddenly serious and winking at his wife, made an announcement!<br>As I was told..It went something like this***<br><br>&quot;I have a surprise for my dearest friends&quot;!! Taking his beloved wife's hand, with Kahesha smiling said: &quot;I have learned..&quot;I am to be a Father&quot;!!<br>Samuel and Laah were overjoyed for their new found friends! Both parents deciding that if a girl-child was born to Kahesha that I and you my sweet, would be bound together and NO Other to take our place!<br><br>&quot;This my Love was what I wanted to tell you&quot;..BUT!.. I have to be honest in my part and feelings on this when I was younger!<br><br>After my parents told me of their decisions on Our Bonding, I was upset..As all young boys would be!! Resentment grew in me for months! I barely spoke to my parents!<br>Then!!! The terrible news came down from Halas, that your mother had died upon your birth!<br>Bearing this burden...my parents decided, no bonding of their children would occur on such a sad day! This greatly eased my mind..and...as Seasons passed, the memory faded of you.<br><br>Drinel, being the wanderer he was, found himself in our Glade.<br>Samuel knowing of his friendship with your father..Ask him to sup with us and tell of Lo'Rrin's health. The news was not good! Lo'Rrin's mourning was without End!!<br><br>Drinel, then made it a habit of coming to our Glade frequently for visits. On one such visit...I asked him if he would teach me the ways of his Shaman heritage. Gentle man that he was, he agreed. This evidently leading me to your village of Halas for further learning.<br>There-in - Is how I came upon you!!<br>Try as I might!...Once again remembering our parents Oath to each other, and my younger selfs resentments - My heart was lost To-YOU!!!<br><br>&quot;Yes Azzarria&quot; - &quot;My heart is Yours&quot;! Foolish boy-child never knew his heart and soul was Always bound to you, thru the special love and friendship our parents had found.<br><br>&quot;Destiny&quot; is a slippery creature!! Wandering - Touching Souls - Without any Mortal the Wiser!!!<br><br><br>***Part 5...To be continued<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Azzarria - "Stormchild"<br>"The Huntress"</td></tr>
