	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=105234642511670>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=105234642511670>New Friends  #3</a> <a id=fs8 href=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=105234642511670#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, May 7th 7:07 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189461><span id=Sage>Taimarawee</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Saying that pressing business calls from the East, my new friend &quot;Simofez&quot;..the Erudite Wizard of Erudin..had agreed to Adventure with me.<br><br>Time passes....I am venturing again my native lands of Everfrost, exploring it's white beauty and the dangers that lay there.. When in the distance - There &quot;Si&quot; is!<br>Fighting a Mammoth! - Nasty Creatures of Death and Destruction!! - He was losing both ground and blood!<br>I call to him..If I may aid his battle, he nods - knowing if he turned to me he would be gored! <br><br>Stepping in with Ponpi', our efforts are rewarded with the heavy fall of flesh hitting the frozen ground as it breaths its last. &quot;Sweet Victory&quot;!<br><br>Together we travel this frozen land of mine for many moon passings, learning to hunt together and relish the rewards.<br><br>One bitter cold evening, not being able to find cave shelter and having to sit upon the ice-plane &quot;Si&quot; suggests we venture onto warmer lands. My body having taken a bitter chill from an open wound and frostbite almost upon me, I agree.<br><br>Traveling to different lands...We encountered an old enemy of many people - The &quot;Orc's&quot;! Pray tell those Ugly Brutes, whos strengths equal mine or possibly many times more..was almost the death of me!!!<br><br>&quot;Si&quot; upon seeing my distress raced in to help!! Reaching out with that Great Staff, barely saved this bruised, torn body from the clutches of an &quot;Orc Chieftan! Pulling me to my feet and gently guiding me to a safer place, he tended my wounds with herbs. I believe had it not been for my new found friend on this eve...I would be no more!<br><br>Brushing myself off - and - being both the Wiser for that fight and shame for even being in that unsafe land..told &quot;Si&quot; I had to go get more supplies and stop to see an old friend of our family.<br>He knowingly... Agreed to let me go on.<br><br>Proud People We Be and I with my Learnings of My Elders, should of been aware of this unsafe land and should have been more cautious, knowing Simofez was NOT by my side!!<br><br>I traveled to Freeport where there lived another dear friend of my families. One to whom I could run to for comfort in my young seasons.<br><br>He also is a Shaman of great knowledge. &quot;Adurinn&quot;...Teacher of my teachers. Old, kind and wise...Adurinn upon seeing me knew exactly what had happened and comforted me! <br><br>After some time with this kind Shaman...Upon parting - he gave me his advice. &quot;Azzarria&quot;, my child, &quot;Experience is a Teacher&quot;...&quot;Harsh though it may be&quot;...&quot;Will always be your guide between the staying and passing of this plane&quot;. &quot;Do not fear to venture forth in these lands, for without knowledge, there is no worth!&quot;.<br><br>Being stronger for this advice and the nuturing he gave me...I went forth once more, with my head held high!!!<br><br>Now in my tale...I come to a unique Dwarf that I met shortly after leaving Adurinn!<br><br>I met this dwarf in a Tavern in East Freeport, grumbling to hisself in a far off corner. Something about &quot;Gnomes&quot;!! &quot;Bruenor&quot; is his name...He hails from across the Ocean of Tears - A Mountain City called..&quot;Kaladim&quot;. <br><br>Rich ores are mined there as can be attested to the Impressive Axe and Mighty Hammer draped across his back.<br><br>After several &quot;Dwarven Ale's&quot;, he agreed to teach me the ways of his people and their fighting and hunting styles.<br><br>**Across the Winds...Trouble was brewing!!! Too many Travelers across the Lands were being missed in the tellings around the fires.<br><br>It seems &quot;Cabalis&quot; - &quot;Montument to Pain&quot; - was the source!<br>Now..&quot;Bruenor&quot; had been there many times, so I decided to follow and learn from him.<br><br>Upon reaching the back-side of the &quot;Iskar&quot; lands...Bruenor points in the distance.... Our destination: &quot;Kurns Tower&quot;.<br>By the Gods, what an evil looking place...Raising high into the heavens!! A fortress of evil, I must say!!<br><br>As Bruenor and I travel to this place, we must climb high into the fortress to gain access. Being born on solid land, climbing high put the fear into me, but my trust was with my friend, so follow I did.<br><br>Hitting the top of this evil tower I and Ponpi' come skidding to a stop!<br>There in the hallway is an Undead Creature that rivals ones I have seen before!! <br>There is a force about this one that makes me fear for our life!<br>Seeing this I am told: &quot;Aye Lass&quot; &quot;A sight they are, but show No Fear&quot;...&quot;Follow Me Lead&quot;.<br><br>As we ventured farther in, the Scalebone swiftly attacks Bruenor!<br>His long boney clawed fingers reach out - Suddenly!! It gouges a bloody grove across Bruenors chest..dropping him to his knees! - For &quot;Seconds In Time&quot;...&quot;An Eternity to Me&quot;, &quot;Bruenor did not move!!!!<br><br>When I thought all was Lost! - Raising that proud head of his and pulling himself up with his pain - he strikes!!! Swiftly that many notched Axe of his whistles and cleaves this evil creature in two!!<br><br>Blood freely running down his Dwarven Mail..I see a light come into his eyes. Thru blood and grime.. he has conquered once more!<br><br>&quot;Lass&quot;..&quot;Be Ye Well&quot;?? Blinking away the remaining fear from my addled brain...&quot;Aye!&quot;..&quot;Twas just the battle my friend&quot;.<br><br>Here-In lies the reason of many missing travelers**<br><br>&quot;BEWARE!&quot;...Of these Nasty Undead things!! For they will end yer life quickly if ye are not prepared!<br><br><br>Part Three.......to be continued.<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Azzarria - "Stormchild"<br>"The Huntress"</td></tr>
