</ul></td></tr></table>

<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f105234616511704>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=105234616511704>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=105234616511704>Gather...Once More for my Tale</a> <a id=fs8 href=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=105234616511704#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, May 7th 7:02 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189461><span id=Sage>Taimarawee</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&quot;StormChild&quot;...the silky voice of the Lake whispers.<br>&quot;One last swim for old times sake?&quot; <br><br>Shedding my furs, I slip into the dark lake, rolling over and feeling the cold water caressing my skin...Cooling the fevered rush of adreneline that courses thru me.<br><br>Looking up at my Great Northern Sky.... Luclin has not yet given way to her brother Sun. I still have the pleasure of seeing masses of stars so bright they hurt mine eyes....vyiing one another for attention!<br><br>Floating leisurely, my thoughts drift with the stars. I must decided which direction I want to travel.<br>Drinel upon learning of my leaving has given me Knowledge and Maps to sustain through the perils of the lands awaiting me.<br><br>Abruptly..as though the Lake has heard my thoughts and decision, whispers -- &quot;Azzarria&quot; &quot;Go forth&quot;...&quot;Learn&quot;....&quot;Fight&quot;...&quot;Experience this for me and return to share the Glories and Hardships with your people&quot;.<br>This being said...I know my Decisions..Though Painful to my Father.. were correct. <br><br>It's Time!<br><br>Pulling myself from the Lakes edge, I gather a small soft fur and dry off. Fumbling from Cold.. I find it hard to equip my armor and weapons.<br>This.. having finally done - &quot;I STILL&quot; - Slowing my breathing. Deep within my soul I call to Ponpi'Kala. Looking down - once more - I smile, seeing his Strength and Beauty.<br>In the Language know only to my Hybrid side...I say: &quot;Kakita&quot; - &quot;Onwards My Pet&quot;....&quot;Onwards!&quot;<br><br>Traveling the icy cavern and down onto the land of Everfrost, I encounter my first &quot;Avenger&quot;! Nasty! Dead Thing!--&quot;Away with thee&quot;! The fight was Bloody for us both---the Win, &quot;Mine&quot;!<br><br>By late day, I feel the Chill creeping into my bones and hunger resides persistant within me! Upon laying a small fire for warmth, I share this meager meal of dried meat and berries with Ponpi'. The warmth of the small fire has me unexpectedly dozing. Curling up against Ponpi's silken fur, I finallly give in to unknown dreams awaiting me.<br><br>**Dawn slowly Breaks<br>My senses Alerted!...I feel a difference in the frozen Earth..&quot;Vibrations&quot;.. Unknown to me! Looking into the distance I see a Mammoth and her Calf approaching close to where I camp. I know from tales of the Elders, neither I nor Ponpi' dare venture this beast in my young season. GODS!...Though she is beautiful!!!!<br><br>Quickly dressing, I put out my lazy campfire and retreat to safer grounds - and let her to her wanderings - safe from Me.... for now!!<br><br>Upon higher ground I continue to watch her and the calf. My mind sharping - I will remember her patterns for when, once more she and I meet!! Noticing the lateness of the hour..I decide to run through Blackburrow. Home of the temperant gnolls and their commanders.<br><br>Winding, winding paths!! So confusing to one so young! I fairly panic, with the loss of light surrounding me! This Dusky Hour, by my proud superstitious people, is called: &quot;The Niknik&quot;.....Confusion of Direction. They believe the un-dead are at play with one's mind....My Talisman protection from all things, but this!!<br><br>Stumbling and shaken... I come forth from the tunnels onto a sight to behold for one so young!!! <br>Never having ventured from her home of Ice and Snow - Amazement washes over me as I drink in this new beauty of green plains and warmth. Gods!! The warmth!!! In all the tales of my Father to me, I always thought they were only to simply comfort a small one's passing to sleep!<br><br>My breathing slows. With that comes complete and utter exhaustion! Poor Ponpi' has also run his last for this day.<br><br>Looking to my maps, it shows a lake West of me...Hopefully there I may rest undisturbed from hungry wolves and wanderings of the un-dead.<br><br>Running across the hills I notice a small wooden hut and farther South of me....A small entrance into the mountain. Another time perhaps!!<br><br>Finally, coming upon the lake, exhaustion truly sets in. NO fire - nor - FOOD this night---Must Rest! Snuggling deep into my furs, I fall into sweet oblivian.<br><br>Consciousness slowly raising within my soul---I hear the strange new sounds of the hills and smile. Not wanting to open my eyes, but know I must- I stir and sit up. Looking around for Ponpi'...I find him swimming in the lake! Gods!!! Never having seen him wet...I laugh!....He looks like a Giant White Rat!!!<br>Still laughing..I decide to join this Wet Companion of mine!<br><br>Washing the grime and previous evenings fear from my body, I rise dripping from the lake--anticipating a warm fire and meal to begin my new day in this strange land.<br><br>**Lingering longer than I should have-Early Morning losing ground to later day, I know I must continue on my journey.<br><br>Breaking camp, I remember the Hut I had ran near night last and decide to replenish my meager provisions--then head towards the city they call: &quot;NQeynos&quot;. Curiosity driving me from the tales told to me by Drinel..our Shaman Healer and Friend. I believe - I remember him saying it was the lineage of ones called...&quot;Antonius Bayle&quot;.<br><br>Calling Ponpi' to my side, I find a path I had missed in the dark and head towards that distant memory of seeing the merchant hut.<br><br>Ah! The Hut! Almost at once though, instinct makes me pause on the path. What of these people? Will I be welcomed, or shunned?? As my story goes..I neglected in telling of my strange Heritage. &quot;Barbarian&quot;...Aye!! Though, not truly. Here-in also lies the other side...An uncommon side..! My mother &quot;Kahesha's&quot;-- &quot;Beastlord&quot; blood runs strongly thru me - allowing me control of the companion at my side. Little is known to me of this strange and wonderful heritage.<br><br>Losing my Mother at birth, my Father - grieving still, would not complete my questions on this matter. Saying &quot;It should of been told to you, by her&quot;. Giving up in exasperation - I gather as much as I could from Drinel and let it lie....Content in knowing my Mother would be with me always.<br><br>Trepidation within me...I approach and enter their hut. Thank the Gods!! The Merchant is cautious, but willing to provide the supplies I need! Upon completing the barter and consulting my maps, I set forth for the city.<br><br>Ponpi' growls, bringing my attention back to the path ahead. Gods!! What manner of creature is this?? That have Black Stick Legs holding up a Crimson and Yellow hard-shelled body??!!<br><br>My curiosity winning over, I approach this creature. For my troubles....I find myself bitten severly! Well! This will not do! God's creature or NO, I will NOT take this Pain and Humiliation!!<br><br>Having barely won this strange new fight, I gather my wits about me and see in the distance my destination.<br><br>Towering Grey-Stone and Brown-Brick Castle Walls loom towards the Heavens. Heavily battered and worn from long-ago wars...it still stands proud with Flags and Banners waving in the warm soft winds. A profound sense of loss for these people nearly over-takes my senses.<br><br>Amoung the great trees I see corpses of slain &quot;Darkpaw&quot;...Ah! They have yet to learn!! Still invading borders that were closed to them a long time ago. I will try to assist this cause, both for gaining these proud people's respect and bounty for my dwindling purse.<br><br>Upon receiving permission to approach their walls and city...I and Ponpi' gather to Hunt this enemy and the hard-shelled creature, they call - &quot;Fire Beetles&quot;. &quot;AYE&quot;! From my Deep wound....&quot;Fire Beetle&quot; is well named!!<br><br>Hunting near their great castle walls...I hear upon the Winds a &quot;Hail&quot; from behind.<br>Turning - I see a &quot;Erudite Wizard&quot; standing proud before me...dressed in Robes of Gold and Browns shimmering in the late afternoon sun. Weilding a Staff of wonderous strength!<br>Upon our greetings, I learn his name and find his seasons to be near my own.<br><br>By the Gods!!! My First Friend!!! -- I wonder......&quot;Should I dare ask this Erudite Wizard if he would care to join me in my Quest of these Norrathian Lands&quot;??<br><br><br>&quot;Part Two&quot; to be continued******<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Azzarria - "Stormchild"<br>"The Huntress"</td></tr>
