	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=103568460627161>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=103568460627161>Come Sit...I will give you a Tale of "Becoming"</a> <a id=fs8 href=/journal2.html?user=189461&mid=103568460627161#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Oct 26th 10:29 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189461><span id=Sage>Taimarawee</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>***Hardened and Battleworn..Wanting Only to see my Village Once More***<br><br><br>I sit...Severly injured, in a small cavern of Ice and Snow I have found, from the Raging Snowstorm outside.<br><br>During my earlier Battle, with an Old Nemesis -&quot;Gorr&quot; - I found I have lost both my Provisions and Healing Herbs for my Wounds.<br><br>I &quot;Know Not&quot; if I will Survive this Injury.<br><br>As I huddle deep into my furs for warmth that is not there, I reflect back to the Beginning of &quot;My Time&quot; in this Beautiful Land of Crystal Ice and Blinding Snow.<br><br><br>**I was Born on a night closely resembling this moment..As was told to me by my father Lo'Rrin MacGuiness.<br><br>The night was frigid, with Snow blowing across our tiny village of &quot;Halas&quot; and closing all our passes to all travelers who may of wished passage granted to them.<br><br>My Father was distraught!..He knew this was going to be a hard birth for my mother &quot;Kahesha&quot;. Alas, she is not of our hardy barbarian heritage.<br><br>My father's Shaman - &quot;Drinel&quot; - Friend and healer to our family, had been delayed in his trip back to &quot;Halas&quot;. The pass was now closed, and all further help from him was lost to us!<br><br>As &quot;Nature&quot; must..&quot;I&quot; came forth on this very night of our God's raging in the Heavens! <br>Upon the moment of my birth - The heavens split asunder! Lo'Rrin, awed by such an Un-natural Force named his child - &quot;Azzarria&quot;....&quot;Child of the Storm&quot;.<br><br>My Lovely Mother Kahesha...Being of frail health...Could not withstand the battering of my birth, nor the forces of nature outside pounding on our door.<br><br>The God's giving me and taking her...I will regret not meeting this beautiful woman!<br><br>I grew strong and learned well over the years with both my Fathers teachings and Drinel's mastery of his Shaman arts.<br><br>As my Seasons came and went with vicious goblins always at our passes, I mastered the art of weaponry and spells. As payment for this-the God's granted me a wolf cub companion, to guard my journeys across Norrathian lands..&amp;..&quot;I&quot;...To guard his.<br><br>Azzarria looking down upon this beautiful Snow White Creature..guarding her so closely, for his young seasons, named him &quot;Ponpi'Kala&quot;....&quot;White Guardian&quot;.<br><br>I, Being restless in my village these seasons past, went seeking my father. I told him of my Natural Calling to seek and hunt further out from our lands. AH!.....My heart near burst with pain for the look that came upon my fathers face!...We embraced - As I stood back and looked fully upon the face of this Gentle Barbarian Father - who would Fight and Die to the Death for his Daughter and People....I still saw there his understanding. He said: &quot;Azzarria&quot; my beautiful and proud daughter--&quot;Know This!&quot;<br><br>&quot;What You See isn't always what you get&quot;. &quot;Sometimes it's much better&quot;....&quot;Sometimes much, much worse!&quot;.<br>&quot;Guard well these words&quot;... &quot;They will be your Guidence from Me, until we meet again upon our Ancestral Planes&quot;.<br><br>Shaken by her father's deep emotion and his words of guidence, still was determined to venture forth. Destiny seemed to be calling her on the winds. Azzarria could NOT resist!<br><br>Tall...Proud...Azzarria stood very still in the dusty morning light by the lake edge before leaving, and turned slowly. - Her deep blue eyes resting on every familiar hut and shop she had visited.<br>Remembering small tales of each of these visits and the gentle barbarian people she loved so well. She would hold them to her heart for strength and endurance - Wishing that Fate had chosen a different path for her to follow.<br><br><br>&quot;Part One.....to be continued*****<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed May&nbsp;&nbsp;7 18:25:16 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Azzarria - "Stormchild"<br>"The Huntress"</td></tr>
